column31: ******* UPDATE ****** I went and observed today. It is not for a recount, as I originally thought (and was told). As soon as I got there, I was asked who sent me. Then when the second observer arrived, she was asked twice who sent her. She actually asked them why they were being hostile to her (which they were). I am extremely frustrated and I don't even know where to start. I watched the ballot counting in Deschutes County, so I don't know how your county is doing it. This was not a recount. They are still counting ballots! I asked why numbers were given at 8:01 pm on the 3rd then. They said that was the number that they had counted up to that date, since the Thursday the 29th. They were not allowed to start counting prior to the Thursday before election day. The numbers called in had only been for the ballots that were counted the Thursday, Friday and Monday before election day. I asked why they called in those numbers then if all the ballots hadn't been counted. I was told they had until the 23rd. That's the official day that they have to certify and submit the official number. I then asked if they had even started counting the ballots that came in on Monday the 2nd or on election day, the 3rd. They had not! They said they will start counting them probably Tuesday or Wednesday next week! I then asked what the numbers looked like as of today, since they have had 9 more days that they've counted. I was told they don't know and won't know until the 23rd. I call BS, but who am I? The process is extremely messed up and completely confusing. We were very far away from where they were tallying them, they were actually in another room. There was a window that we watched through. There was someone on a laptop and a person behind her. What was being done on the laptop showed up on a TV monitor above their heads so we could see. We really couldn't see and what we saw was very, very confusing. We had no idea what they were doing, what boxes they were checking and unchecking, no clue what the acronyms meant or the dozen other things that we were looking at. I thought when I got there, they would at least give a brief overview of what I was suppose to look for or even what they were doing. Nope.... so, after being extremely frustrated, I finally asked an employee walking by. No answers... we asked someone else.... crickets. Finally, a supervisor came out and we asked him a couple questions. Finally the County Clerk came in and we were basically scolded. She said we weren't allowed to speak to each other or the workers. She then asked if we read the rules that we signed prior to going in because if we had questions, we needed to speak only to her. We said yes we read the rules, but we needed direction. We had no clue what we were looking at. We told her we couldn't be affective if we didn't understand the process. The employees were going extremely fast. It reminded me of the olden days where they would put together a picture book and flip through the pages to make it look like a movie. I had some concerns. There was ALOT of ballots that had multiple bubbles filled in, some with check marks, x's, some were completely scribbled over. There was one situation that really made me question what was going on. As they were flipping through them, I saw a ballot where Thatcher was selected, then a big x across it and then Fagan was selected. I didn't see that once, twice or three times. It happened 9 out of the 10 ballots that I was able to pay attention to. 10 in a row! I asked who did the markings. I was told the voter. The computer picked up both choices and both candidates received the vote. That is called over counting. They were going through and removing the wrong vote (the one that was x'd out) and only selecting the other vote. Of course I asked how do I know that someone else didn't do the marking and that the voter in fact had did it. I got a very generic answer and was told that that's how it was when they opened the envelope. I doubt someone who voted Trump would have scratched out Thatchers name and changed it to Fagan. On a positive note, I saw a lot more votes for Trump than I did Biden. Whether they were recorded correctly, I have no clue. Another positive note is that if they have not yet counted the ballots that were received on election day, could that possibly tip over into Trumps favor? Historically, republicans vote on election day. I did also ask what software they use and it's Clear Ballot not Dominion. So, that's it in a nutshell. I will not be going back to observe anymore. It was too frustrating. If there was a comment or concern there was nobody to notify anyway! Updated 11/12/20 Something strange is happening. I am a trained ballot observer and I was just asked if I could watch them recount the ballots in my county at the elections office. They will be doing it for the next 2 weeks. Hmmmm...
Now what???

column31: PFIZER SCIENTISTS WARNING !! Read comments below
column36:
All those people who intend rushing out to pump themselves full of the Covid 19 vaccine might want to read this first.

Letter by Dr Michael Yeadon - Ex-Vice President of Pfizer
Response to the vaccine consultation:
Dear Mr Hancock,
I have a degree in Biochemistry & Toxicology & a research-based PhD in pharmacology. I have spent 32years working in pharmaceutical R&D, mostly in new medicines for disorders of lung & skin. I was a VP at Pfizer & CEO of a biotech I founded (Ziarco - acquired by Novartis). I’m knowledgeable about new medicine R&D.
I have read the consultation document. I’ve rarely been as shocked & upset.
All vaccines against the SARS-COV-2 virus are by definition novel. No candidate vaccine has been in development for more than a few months.
If any such vaccine is approved for use under any circumstances that are not EXPLICITLY experimental, I believe that recipients are being misled to a criminal extent.
This is because there are precisely zero human volunteers for whom there could possibly be more than a few months past-dose safety information.
My concern does not arise because I have negative views about vaccines (I don’t).
Instead, it’s the very principle that politicians seem ready to waive that new medical interventions at this, incomplete state of development- should not be made available to subjects on anything other than an explicitly experimental basis. That’s my concern.
And the reason for that concern is that it is not known what the safety profile will be, six months or a year or longer after dosing.
You have literally no data on this & neither does anyone else.
It isn’t that I’m saying that unacceptable adverse effects will emerge after longer intervals after dosing. No: it is that you have no idea what will happen yet, despite this, you’ll be creating the impression that you do.
Several of the vaccine candidates utilise novel technology which have not previously been used to create vaccines. There is therefore no long term safety data which can be pointed to in support of the notion that it’s reasonable to expedite development & to waive absent safety information on this occasion.
I am suspicious of the motives of those proposing expedited use in the wider human population. We now understand who is at particularly elevated risk of morbidity & mortality from acquiring this virus. Volunteers from these groups only should be provided detailed information about risk / benefit, including the sole point I make here. Only if informed consent is given should any EXPERIMENTAL vaccine be used.
I don’t trust you. You’ve not been straightforward & have behaved appallingly throughout this crisis. You’re still doing it now, misleading about infection risk from young children. Why should I believe you in relation to experimental vaccines?
Dr Michael Yeadon

column31: We make choices every day that put ourselves at risk. We are aware of said risks and choose the path we want to take, knowing the risk is there. But we go on with our lives and do the best we can to stay safe. I get into my vehicle every morning. I make a choice whether or not I want to take the highway or take the back roads. There’s the risk that I could get into a car accident. That accident could be minor, a fender bender, or it could be catastrophic. Each accident would require medical attention or evaluation by a Doctor. The injury could be minuscule to none, or it could be extremely disabling. Either level of injury could/would have long term after effects. Ongoing pain, disability, PTSD, etc. We take precautions, many that are legally required to be followed. Like speed limits, seatbelts, not driving while distracted. Not everyone abides by these, majority do, but it does not guarantee your safety or well being. We go on living and make the best choices we can. We make every attempt to keep ourselves safe and others on the road. We don’t shut down highways or tell people to stay home and not drive due to the number of auto collisions. We don’t keep kids home from school out of the fear that their school bus may crash. We don’t tell people to ride their bikes or walk because it’s safer than driving. We don’t stop living. We go on. We do our best but we don’t live in fear. 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸 See my point?

column31: On Friday 11/8 we filed a motion for summary judgment in our separation of powers lawsuit against the Governor. Our motion asks the court to decide the case directly because there are no disputed facts for a jury to consider. Once I have a link to the legal memo I will post it for those who want to see the arguments we are making. The Attorney General’s office has not yet committed to defending the Governor. Normally, a defendant is supposed to answer a complaint within 30 days, so we will probably hear from either the Governor or the Attorney General within the next ten days. We plan to seek a default judgment as soon as legally permissible if we do not get a timely answer. Unfortunately, because of covid-19 delays in court scheduling, and because the Attorney General’s office may file a motion in the case, a court hearing may be delayed until January. This is disappointing, but the Oregon Rules of Civil Procedure are designed to be fair to everyone. A fixed number of days must elapse after each motion before next actions can be taken. Had we approached this case like the one in Ohio, with facts in dispute, it would surely take even longer. As soon as I have more information about a hearing date I will share it.

column31: HOW DEADLY IS COVID-19...REALLY? #doctorsspeakout 1. "At the beginning of October, one of the World Health Organization’s executive directors, said that the WHO estimated that 750 million people had so far been infected with covid. At that point, one million people had died of the disease. That gives a death rate for covid of 0.13%. So the WHO said that the death rate is 0.13%. This of course begs the question why there are continued lockdowns for a disease that is no worse than the flu." 2. "A short while later, the WHO released an analysis by professor John Ioannidis, with his estimate of the covid death rate. This analysis was based on seroprevalance data, i.e. data on how many people were shown to have antibodies to covid in their bloodstream at different times in different countries, which was correlated with the number of deaths in those countries. Through this analysis, professor Ioannidis reached the conclusion that covid has an overall mortality rate of around 0.23% (in other words, one in 434 infected people die of the disease). For people under the age of 70, the mortality rate was estimated at 0.05% (in other words, one in 2,000 infected people under the age of 70 die of the disease)." 3. "For comparison, the 1918 flu pandemic is thought to have had an infection fatality rate of 2.5% (1 in 40 infected people died). So the 1918 flu was 11X more deadly than covid if you go by professor Ioannidis antibody based numbers, and 19X more deadly than covid if you go by the fatality rate provided by the WHO. And this is missing one big point about covid. The average person who dies from covid is over 80 years old and has multiple underlying health conditions. In other words, their life expectancy is very short. The average person who died in the 1918 pandemic was in their late 20’s. So each death in the 1918 pandemic actually meant around 50 years more of life lost per person than each death in the covid pandemic. Multiply that by the fact that it had a 19X higher death rate, and the 1918 flu was in fact 950X more deadly than covid, in terms its capacity to shorten people’s lives." 4. "What about the fatality rate of the common cold viruses that are constantly circulating in society? How does covid compare to them? Many people think that the common cold viruses are harmless. But in fact, among elderly people with underlying health conditions, they are frequently deadly. A study carried out in 2017 found that, among frail elderly people, rhinovirus is actually more deadly than regular influenza. In that study, the 30 day mortality for frail elderly people admitted to hospital due to a rhinovirus infection was 10%. For frail elderly people admitted to hospital due to influenza, 30 day mortality was 7%. If you are old and frail, and have underlying health conditions, then even that most harmless of all infections, the so called 'common cold', can be deadly. In fact, it often is. Covid-19 is not a unique disease, and does not appear to have a noticeably higher mortality rate than the so called 'common cold'." 5. "There is one final aspect to all this that needs to be discussed. And that is the effect of covid on overall mortality. If it turns out that covid has no effect on overall mortality, then that really brings in to question why we are locking down, since we’re not actually preventing any deaths. So, what is the effect of covid on overall mortality?" 6. Two additional key considerations..."The first is that most people who died “of” covid actually died "with" covid. In other words, they had a positive covid test and were therefore characterized as covid deaths, when the actual cause of death was something else. The second is that most people who died of covid were so old, and so frail, and had so many underlying health conditions, that even without covid, they would have died by now." "This is not saying that covid is nothing, or that it doesn’t exist. It's saying that it is a virus with a marginal effect on longevity. And yet, public policy in most countries has been driven by doomsday scenarios based on completely unrealistic numbers. To put it simply, we’ve acted like we’re dealing with a global ebola outbreak, when covid is much more like the common cold." #factsnotfear #flattenthefear #whatpandemic #casedemic #logicvslockdown (https://sebastianrushworth.com/2020/10/24/how-deadly-is-covid-19/)

column36:
Here is a draft of what I plan to ask Texas legislators to sponsor.  It will take 2/3 of each chamber to make it to the ballot for the people of Texas to vote for it next November.  I welcome suggested modifications:

Joint Resolution Draft for Bill of Rights Addition Recognizing the Right to Refuse Vaccination

A JOINT RESOLUTION

proposing a constitutional amendment relating to the natural, unalienable right to refuse vaccination.

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF TEXAS:

SECTION 1.  Article I, Texas Constitution, is amended by adding Section 35 to read as follows:

Sec. 35.  The unalienable natural right of the people to refuse vaccination shall not be infringed. Because the right is unalienable, it cannot be bargained away, and therefore vaccination shall not be made a condition of employment, travel, doing business, receiving governmental services, or any other action***.***

SECTION 2.  This proposed constitutional amendment shall be submitted to the voters at an election to be held November 2, 2021. The ballot shall be printed to permit voting for or against the proposition: "The constitutional amendment recognizing the right of the people to refuse vaccination."

column31: ONTARIO'S SECOND WAVE OF COVID-19 AND MANDATORY MASKS Despite the widespread use of mandatory masks across the province, Ontario is experiencing a second wave that is much worse than the first--recently doubling the number of cases per day. (1) The use of masks has been a controversial one, as the government and many health experts recommend tout their use. To date, there have only been randomized control trials on masks with healthcare workers and none have been favourable to the use of cloth masks. In fact, one study in the British Medical Journal (BMJ), “A cluster randomised trial of cloth masks compared with medical masks in healthcare workers,” concluded that “moisture retention, reuse of cloth masks and poor filtration may result in increased risk of infection” and did not recommend their use for healthcare workers. (2) Masks did not help in Ontario’s first wave of Covid-19, as their use was mandated well after the peak and at one of the lowest points of transmission. With a second wave now upon the province, could the results of the BMJ study be bearing out in the surging transmission of cases? Are masks contributing to Ontario’s second wave of Covid-19? (1) https://www.publichealthontario.ca/en/data-and-analysis/infectious-disease/covid-19-data-surveillance/covid-19-data-tool (2) https://bmjopen.bmj.com/content/5/4/e006577

column31: Good morning everyone. I've had a few of you reach out to me asking me for the template that I used when contacting head offices of any companies/businesses that refuse me service for not wearing a mask. My template is a bit too big for a private message so I am posting it here for you. I'll show you the exact email I sent to Booster Juice, Dollar Store and Tim Horton's. All three got back to me within 24 hours and all three apologized to me. The key here is to do a little research and find out who the COO or CEO is in Canada. You tell them that your human rights have been violated and you are considering legal action. Here is the letter I wrote along with some attachments I sent. This is not allowing me to attach the letter from MPP Randy Hillier. I'll see if I can add to it by picture. But this is the EXACT letter I sent to all three CEO's and got apologies all three times. HERE IS THE EXACT LETTER I WROTE Dear Mr. Cil (CEO Tim Horton's Canada) I attempted to call your Corporate Office and was directed to this email address. I hope I have reached the correct person as I'm trying to get in touch with Corporate Compliance. This letter is in response to a very unsettling and disturbing incident that I had at one of your stores in Brampton, Ontario Canada. The location was on Father Tobin and Torbram Road. I was in the process of asking for coffee and a bagel and then a different employee (presumably a manager or shift supervisor) told me that I had to wear a mask. She demanded it. I informed her that I have a medical exemption. She then asked me what my condition was. I informed her that she was not allowed to ask me that. According to the Personal Health Information Act, you cannot ask a person what their condition is. I felt it was best to contact you, Mr Cil, first before considering taking legal action against the business for an infringement of my Charter rights. I'd rather avoid this course of action. To be sure that I was not misunderstanding her intention, I asked her again 'are you refusing to allow me into the store and also refusing to adhere to the letter of the law'? She stated again that she absolutely can ask for my medical condition. I have the by-law on my phone which shows that there are exceptions where people do not have to wear a mask. I asked her if she was aware of this by-law to which she replied, "I don't know what a by-law is." I always want to make sure that I am handling things in the right way and give employees the benefit of the doubt as I know sometimes they are not trained correctly. I asked her again her intention, she stated, yet again - she could ask for my condition, which as I'm sure you aware according to the by law...is illegal. Below please find a copy of the Ontario Bylaw, indicating medical exemptions, religious exemptions, mental health exemptions and exemptions for children: Some individuals may be unable to wear a mask. The Region is asking residents to be supportive to others in our community who may be exempt and remind residents every person’s situation is different. For those unable to wear a mask, the bylaw does not require them to disclose the reason for the exemption. Here are just some of the reasons why one should not be forced to wear a mask. Children under the age of two. These very young children must not wear a face covering because of the risk of suffocation. Individuals with a medical condition that makes it difficult to wear a mask. This can include but is not limited to: Medical condition, mental health condition, cognitive condition or disability that prevents wearing a mask or face covering. Medical condition that makes it difficult to breathe or someone who is unconscious or incapacitated. People who are hearing impaired, or are communicating with a person who is hearing impaired, and where the ability to see the mouth is essential for communication. Individuals who are unable to put on or remove a mask without assistance. Note: Businesses are not permitted to require proof that an exemption applies. As you can see, Businesses are NOT permitted to ask for proof of exemption. To do so is to violate the law. Additionally - People with exemptions that require accommodation in accordance with the Ontario Human Rights code must be given such accommodation or be found in violation of the Code. Businesses must still adhere to every aspect of the Ontario Human Rights Code. Also, on the Ontario Human Rights Commission Website under Covid Questions and Answers, under Section 13, It states "no one should be discriminated against for wanting to wear a mask of FOR NOT WANTING TO WEAR A MASK". My rights were violated by your Father Tobin location in general, and by your employee, in particular. I am planning on going back and I do sincerely hope that your store employees and managers are educated as to the specifics of the law. My sincere hope is that your Chief Compliance Officer will respond positively to this letter. I am sure that we are (truncated)

column36:
So it seems coronavirus can be passed by animals after all 🤷🏻‍♂️

Denmark has made the decision to kill 17 million mink after a mutated strain was picked up in humans and mink.

Their Prime Minister ordered the national cull with a "heavy heart" but said mutations in the animals were a threat to the effectiveness of vaccines in development around the globe.
"The mutated virus - via mink - can carry the risk that the upcoming vaccine will not work as it should," Frederiksen said in a press conference.

Health Minister Magnus Heunicke said about half of 783 infected people in northern Denmark, home to many mink farms, had been infected with a strain stemming from the farms.

A targeted cull has been under way at some farms since July but the police, army and national guard will be deployed over the coming days to cull the entire population quickly. Mink have also been culled in some other countries, including the Netherlands and Spain.
However, Francois Balloux, the director of the University College London Genetics Institute and a professor of computational systems biology, cast doubt on the findings.

"There are thousands of mutations in SARS-CoV-2 arising constantly," he said on Twitter. "The fact that a few have been observed in minks will not change the strains in circulation in humans. If they were beneficial for the virus to infect its human host, they would be at high frequency already."

From State Rep John Becker House Bill 618 - “Need Ohio Working (NOW) Act” has 12 co-sponsors and is scheduled for a second hearing this Tuesday, November 17th in the State and Local Government Committee. The bill reverses all past, current, and future orders from the Ohio Department of Health regarding the pandemic unless first approved by the Ohio General Assembly. Other than prohibiting the cancelling of an election, local boards of health will continue to have power to issue orders pertaining to the pandemic. More information is here: [https://www.legislature.ohio.gov/.../legislation-summary](https://www.legislature.ohio.gov/.../legislation-summary?fbclid=IwAR1qz8Ti2tH-qYuk0VG1HrwJZzmZTYScymtxVHLVhvai_GD5aSZNrhaowsI)... column31: Copied: Something is seriously off with this picture. So the flu disappears, COVID-19 suddenly becomes the culprit, and we have people being tested en masse. Yet check this out:: In 2018, there were 23 deaths from influenza and pneumonia per 100,000 population, an increase from previous years. Influenza, more commonly known as the flu, is a highly contagious viral infection and frequent cause of pneumonia. Pneumonia is a more serious infection of the lungs and is particularly deadly among young children, the elderly, and those with certain chronic conditions. Sound familiar? Pneumonia is among the leading diagnoses for inpatient hospitalizations in Canada. From 2016 to 2017, there were almost 68,000 inpatient hospitalizations for pneumonia. This was around 2.2 percent of all inpatient hospitalizations during that time. The average length of stay for inpatient hospitalization for pneumonia is around 6.7 days. Sound familiar? Here’s a description of pneumonia from the Charles Davis, MD, PHD - “Pneumonia is inflammation of the lung tissue usually but not exclusively caused by infection from bacteria, virus, or fungus.” Really you don’t say? So you’re telling me that the flu as stated above can cause pneumonia, and that the flu holds the same character classification as coronavirus, a large family of viruses that can cause respiratory infections? Are you connecting the dots yet? Answer me this; what if this past year’s flu was simply just a hybrid, and if that being the case, would have likely needed to be created via a human host.... because it cannot multiply without a “live” host. Pause. If that could be the case, then did the flu actually disappear? Or, is this simply the outcome of either an experiment gone wrong or a controlled test? Here’s the statement from a report:: “New Canadian research backs suggestions that only people given a flu shot for the 2008-2009 season seemed to be more likely to get infected with the pandemic virus.” Oh wait, you didn’t know? We had like this crazy pandemic a few years back, no big deal, I mean only like 525,000 people died. No big deal right??? I mean think about it - for those of you who’ve taken your flu shot every year, you were primed to get sick! It’s interesting that those who received a flu shot, actually have been prone to more severe symptoms. column31: THAT MASK IS GIVING YOU LUNG CANCER - From Guy Crittenden, who, for 25 years, edited the trade journal HazMat Management. I happen to know a thing or two about masks and safety. Why? Because for 25 years I was the editor of an award-winning trade magazine called HazMat Management that covered such topics as pollution prevention and compliance with health & safety laws. We routinely published articles on masks, gloves, respirators and other forms of personal protective equipment (PPE). Now let me tell you a few things about that mask you’re wearing. And please note that what I’m about to share was also stated in the most recent edition of Del Bigtree’s program The Highwire when two OSHA mask experts spoke to the fact that the kinds of masks people are wearing were never (never!) designed to be worn for long periods and doing so is very harmful. The blue typical mask depicted in the photograph contain Teflon and other chemicals. A Facebook friend reminds us: 1. Masks are “sterilized” with Ethylene Oxide — a known carcinogen. Many teachers in various school boards have been experiencing significant symptoms as a direct result of the effects of this chemical. 2. The masks contain (not sprayed with) PTFE which makes up Teflon along with other chemicals. I found and have posted the US patent to allow manufacturers to use PTFE as a filter in commercial masks… “breathing these for extended periods can lead to lung cancer.” Don’t agree? Argue with the experts at OSHA, which is the main US agency, i.e., its Occupational Health & Safety Agency. These masks are meant to be worn only for short periods, like say if you’re sanding a table for an hour and don’t want to inhale sawdust. They don’t do anything whatsoever to stop the spread of any virus, and the emerging science of virology now understands that viruses aren’t even passed person to person. I know that sounds incredible, but it’s the case that the virus is in the air, you breath it in, there’s no way to prevent that short of living in an oxygen tent, and if you have a strong immune system you’ll be fine, and if you have a weak immune system you may have to deal with the effects of your immune system working to restore balance within your metabolism. So let’s say you don’t wear the blue packaged masks, and instead wear a homemade cloth mask — the kind people wear over and over and hang on their rearview mirror and so on. Those masks are completely useless against a virus, and are also very dangerous. OSHA would never condone a person wearing a mask of this kind for anything more than the shortest time. Re-breathing your own viral debris is dangerous to health, and the oxygen deprivation children suffer wearing such masks all day will certainly cause brain damage. I’m not making this up. Again, you might say, well, Guy, you’re not a doctor. True, but I did edit that magazine for 25 years. That’s a long time and many articles on masks and PPE. I’ve attended numerous OH&S conferences and listened to experts discussing these matters. You may hear people saying that surgeons and nurses wear masks like this all day. Um, no. No they don’t. They’re trained in the proper use of masks, which is to wear them in the OR, then dispose of the mask when they leave that room. Are you aware that operating rooms are actually supplied extra oxygen, to compensate for the reduction in oxygen flow from mask wearing? To my mind, it’s criminal (not hyperbole) to force children to wear masks all day. Setting aside the very real psychological effects, we’re going to have a generation of brain damaged children. Ever heard the expression, “Not enough oxygen at birth?” That’s a joke at the expense of a mentally challenged person, but that’s literally what we’re doing. And we’re told it’s to “keep us safe”! We’re told this by doctors who actually don’t know about PPE and laypeople who have no clue.

column36:
Pharmaceutical giant, Pfizer, has faced thousands of lawsuits. It has also set a record for the largest fine ($2.3 billion) paid for a healthcare fraud lawsuit. What was it for? Illegal marketing claims.

Here are a few of Pfizer's other shining moments throughout recent history...

1996- conducts illegal/unapproved clinical trial on meningitis in 200 children in Nigeria. 11 children died as a result of the trial and dozens more disabled. In 2011, $700,000 was paid to 4 of the families whose children died and a $35 million fund was set up for those adversely affected.

2012- settled claims totalling over $1 billion related to side effects (breast cancer) from their hormone replacement drug, Prempro 

2013- paid $288 million for cases of side effects (suicidal thoughts) related to their smoking cessation drug, Chantix.

2013- agreed to pay $55 million to settle criminal charges related to their drug Protonix.

2014- recalls lots of Effexor XR when it is discovered to be contaminated with another drug the company manufactures, Tikosyn. This combination of drugs can result in death.

There have been thousands upon thousands of lawsuits, many settled quietly, many more dismissed, and likely twice as many injuries and deaths have occurred as a result of this entity than has even been reported. The pharmaceutical industry has deep pockets and they know who to rub shoulders with to avoid real accountability. They own the media. They own the institutions. They own the politicians and judges. And they can pretty much do what they want because nobody will stop them and their endless flow of profits keeps them untouchable.

Pfizer is currently using their astronomically priced drug, Vyndaqel, as the catalyst for seeking reversal of some pretty major laws. Laws that prevent kickbacks. Of course, that's not the language they use in their lawsuit, but reading between the lines, it becomes quite evident what their goal is. And this strategic move to overturn the antikickback laws prior to the approval of their covid vaccine, which they're touting a 90% efficacy rate for, after mere months of development, is telling.

I don't know about you, but based on their track record I think I'll keep my hands out of the Pfizer cookie jar. Health isn't found in pharmaceuticals.

FORD’S BILL 218 REMOVES ACCOUNTABILITY FOR GOVERNMENT COVID-19 MEASURES

The Ford government’s management of Covid-19, though lauded by many, now has a growing chorus of dissenting voices, including MPPs, mayors, doctors and scientists, and their concerns may never see the light of day if Bill 218 comes to pass. 

Bill 218 legally protects the government against any lawsuit by removing all liability and public inquiry into its actions. 

For instance, about 80% of all deaths in Ontario occurred in long-term care homes, where it took the military to expose the horrendous conditions that elderly loved ones were living under. Their deaths may have been accelerated by several Ford policy decisions, including the refusal of the Ontario Medical Association’s offer of family physicians to open Covid-19 assessment centres in long-term care homes, being denied the right to treatment in hospitals if they were Covid-19 positive, and being subjected to immense psychological stress by being trapped and locked away in their facilities away from loved ones. For families that lost loved ones in these situations, it is deeply concerning that the government is offering itself blanket immunity from any transparency and legal action.
 
Bill 218 is guised as an economic restart, but the real consequences of its provisions are a dangerous threat to the responsibilities and accountability of a government to the taxpaying constituents they represent.

In Quebec, a similar bill, Bill 61, was tabled and unilaterally rejected by the opposition late this summer. Bill 61 sought to restart the economy through a series of public infrastructure processes that could go forward by circumventing the public tender process, expropriating landowners in a fast-tracked and nearly incontestable fashion, and trampling on established environmental protections for good measure. Most dangerously, however, it sought to provide legal immunity to the Quebec government, while also allowing the Legault government to extend its state of emergency indefinitely. 

Bill 61 was roundly rejected with the support of hundreds of thousands of outraged citizens,  citing grave concerns for democratic process and government transparency.

In Ontario, MPP Randy Hillier spoke out in response to Ford's proposed Bill 218 in the Legislative Assembly, arguing that the bill ends responsible government by concealing any incompetence or wrongdoing and removing any consequence or remedy. The Ford government only confirmed its deepening undemocratic stance by limiting the public hearing on Bill 218 to only 15 speakers, though 58 people had applied to speak out against the bill that also limits legal liability for the home operators. 

The Ford government is taking Ontario into dangerous authoritarian waters, especially when considering that it has also changed the rules of the Legislature to enable themselves to pass bills with unprecedented speed.

When the role of government is to serve the interests and safety of their constituents, should any bill allow a government to absolve itself of transparency and accountability?

Par exemple, environ 80% de tous les décès en Ontario sont survenus dans des foyers de soins de longue durée, dans lesquelles les militaires ont dû intervenir pour dénoncer les conditions épouvantables dans lesquelles vivaient les personnes âgées. column31: So our final 'window visit' at the care home before lockdown didn't go according to plan. --------------------- When you are faced with irrational responses your actions become irrational. --------------------- When you are repeatedly told 'we're just following the rules' and those rules have kept you away from your loved one for about 8 or 9 months, you question those rules. --------------------- When the rules - like so many in this period of our history - are purporting to be in place to 'protect' but yet are causing untold damage to physical and mental health then you start breaking the rules. --------------------- Yesterday my 73 year old Mum, pushed into the care home to hug my 97 year old Grandma who has dementia. She then quietly wheeled her out. --------------------- My Mum, is a trained nurse and wishes to care for my Nan at home. We only have Power of Attorney for my Nan's finances. Not for her wellbeing. Before lock down we could over come this by visiting my Nan regularly. Now we can't. My Mum was arrested because she refused to take my Nan back to the care home. --------------------- It feels like we are living in the worst Kafka-esque nightmare. People in masks coming to take your relative away from you. I find myself for the first time in my life on the wrong side of the law. --------------------- I have tried to go through all the 'official channels': written countless letters to MPs, Public Health, the Care home... I have signed petitions, spoken to social workers, we raised a 'safe guarding' concern at the beginning of lockdown due to my Nan's clear deterioration but this was inexplicably dropped and 'disappeared'. When she became ill at the care home and was admitted to hospital we asked that she not go back. Yet she was discharged from hospital behind our backs and without our consent. --------------------- When your voice feels lost in a labyrinth of bureaucracy, when you are informed by the police that you are not on your relative's relevant paper work(!!), when the system is so clearly failing, we have to stand up and reform it. --------------------- The police were as kind as they could be, they had a hard job. I thank them for trying their best and de-arresting my Mum so we could go home together. --------------------- The issues are with the 'guidelines' and with so much fear preventing creative problem solving. Relatives need to be given key-worker status. They need to be allowed into their relative's private bedroom to visit, feed and care for their loved ones. --------------------- I share this story and these two short videos (the second one I recorded by accident but the audio is clear) to highlight to as many people as possible that sometimes the rules aren't right. Sometimes the rules need challenging and changing. --------------------- It is my hope that if enough of us live from our hearts, act from our hearts and speak our truth fearlessly from our hearts, this inhumane situation will come to an end. Leandra Ashton --------------------- Please share. https://www.facebook.com/leandra.ashton/posts/10164466167755361

One Eyed Budgie Gift Shop, a local small business, put up signage stating "mask wearing is prohibited in this establishment." The sign includes a short explanation of their reasoning, stating "[we love] you and respectfully appeal, by way of 1000's of research papers, that you consider the harm you may be causing yourself and others, by wearing a mask." Dave Shearer, the owner of the gift shop, says he placed the sign in his store one month ago and has since converted much of his art gallery into a so-called "truth centre," which displays information disputing the health guidelines supported by the province

column36:
Good news to be thankful for!  Yesterday, the Eighth District Appellate Court in El Paso granted a temporary order halting enforcement of El Paso County Judge Ricardo Samaniego's COVID lockdown edicts, which he had extended through December 1.

Recall that this is the case filed by El Paso businesses that want to stay open reported on yesterday that the Texas Supreme Court, by a 5-4 margin had declined to expedite, opting to wait for the Eighth District to get the job done.

The order to stop enforcement of the edict is temporary until a full trial on the merits can be conducted.

Ken Paxton's AG office has intervened on behalf of the State of Texas on behalf of the businesses, so the case name is State of Texas v El Paso County.  The case number is 08-20-00226-CV.

The businesses who filed the suit are PIZZA PROPERTIES, INC.,  WING DADDY'S, TORO BURGER BAR, CHARCOALER, LLC, TRIPLE A RESTAURANTS, INC. ,CC RESTAURANT LP, FD MONTANA, LLC, WT CHOPHOUSE, LLC, VERLANDER ENTERPRISES, LLC, and BAKERY VENTURES I, LTD.

The businesses are being represented by Kemp Smith LLP with lead attorney Mark Osborn and assisted by Shelly Rivas and Deborah Trejo.

Harry County Judge Lina Hidalgo, Travis County, the City of Austin, and Fort Bend County Judge KP George filed amicus briefs on behalf of the El Paso County Judge.

FROM THE NEWSROOM:  HARTFORD, Conn. — Connecticut Gov. Ned Lamont is self-quarantining after his chief spokesperson tested positive for COVID-19.
The Democratic governor’s chief spokesperson, Max Reiss, identified himself as the senior staff member who had tested positive, in a release posted to Twitter late Friday. An initial news release from the governor’s office didn’t identify the staff member, but said that it was the first known case of the coronavirus in the governor’s office.
Reiss wrote he wasn’t sure how or where he contracted the virus, but added that his family had been self-quarantining after his children were exposed at school. He said none of his family was experiencing symptoms, but they will quarantine for the next two weeks.
Contact tracing has begun and all members of the administration who have been within 6 feet (2 meters) of Reiss for 15 minutes or more will self-quarantine for 14 days. In addition to Lamont, chief of staff Paul Mounds and chief operating officer Josh Geballe will self-quarantine. Reiss also encouraged journalists who had contact with him under those same parameters in the last 24 hours to “take the necessary steps.”
Lamont and senior staff are tested twice a week, the release from the governor’s office said, and there are no known additional positive cases.
Three U.S. governors — Republicans Kevin Stitt of Oklahoma and Mike Parson of Missouri and Democrat Ralph Northam of Virginia — had COVID-19 earlier this year. Another governor, Democrat Steve Sisolak of Nevada, announced Friday that he had tested positive for COVID-19.  Photo courtesy of the Associated Press:  FILE - In this Friday, Aug. 7, 2020 file photo, Connecticut Gov. Ned Lamont speaks to reporters before surveying storm damage in the area in Westport, Connecticut.

column31: THE COST OF TOTAL COVID ELIMINATION POLICIES IN NEW ZEALAND New Zealand's Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern is a controversial figure in the global campaign against Covid-19, as her country enforced “the most stringent” lockdown measures in the world over the summer. In a Facebook live video from August, Ardern announced, "We are quarantining everyone. Now we are also mandating testing. That makes us the most stringent in the world…we’re taking it a bit further." (1)(2) With only 25 total deaths with/from Covid-19 (3), all Covid-19 positive cases were put into one of 32 mandatory quarantine facilities in the country of 4.8 million. Quarantined people were not able to enter or exit a facility, which are equipped with CCTV surveillance cameras and 500 New Zealand defense force personnel, without permission. The press were reportedly not allowed to take photos or video of the quarantine camps. In addition to positive cases, suspected Covid-19 positive citizens and family members were also forced into the quarantine facilities. On mandatory testing in the facilities, Prime Minister Ardern added, “If someone refuses in our facilities to be tested, they have to keep staying. So, they won’t be allowed to leave after 14 days. They have to stay on for another 14 days. So, it’s a pretty good incentive. You either get your tests done and make sure you’re cleared or we will keep you in a facility longer. So, I think most people will look at it and say I will take the test." (1) New Zealand had evidently opted for an elimination strategy that looked to eradicate every last case of Covid-19. Many have called the measures “draconian” and “extreme”, especially considering that there have only been 25 deaths to date. Though the number of deaths are low, at what cost have the world’s most stringent measures come? For one, due to the policies, New Zealand forcibly housed, at one point, the equivalent of a "small town" in the quarantine camps. Their borders are still closed to tourism, one of New Zealand's principal economic drivers, while the country's overall economy has plunged to its lowest point since the Great Depression. (4) Unemployment rates have soared while a Reserve Bank of New Zealand publication estimated a potential 37% retraction in the country's GDP under level 4 lockdown. (5)(6) “The lockdown-induced contraction in the second quarter is only the first round of this economic shock,” said Miles Workman, senior economist at ANZ Bank in Wellington [...] We’re yet to really feel the full impact of the closed border and the sharp global contraction. Fiscal and monetary policy still has its work cut out.” (7) Further questions about the freedom of mobility of its citizens were obviously raised as the government required a negative Covid-19 test to release individuals from their isolation facilities. What is ultimately not known is whether the efficacy of the measures against the singular Covid-19 threat will hold up long-term, or whether the spread is inevitable if/when New Zealand's borders are re-opened. Though proponents of the measures argue that their low case numbers and deaths are a “success”, should governments enact public health policies that breach constitutional freedoms and rights that have a devastating impact on the livelihoods of their citizens? 1. https://www.facebook.com/watch/live/?v=2739215439734782&ref=watch_permalink&t=7 2. https://summit.news/2020/08/14/new-zealand-says-it-will-put-all-new-covid-infectees-their-family-members-in-quarantine-facilities/ 3. https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/new-zealand/ 4. https://www.ausleisure.com.au/news/analysis-shows-new-zealand-tourism-industry-reeling-from-covid-19-crisis/ 5. https://www.aap.com.au/tourism-lockdown-linked-to-deep-new-zealand-recession/ 6. https://www.rbnz.govt.nz/-/media/reservebank/files/publications/analytical%20notes/2020/an2020-04.pdf 7. https://www.thenationalnews.com/business/economy/new-zealand-s-economy-contracts-the-most-since-great-depression-1.1078951 ---------------------------------------- LE COÛT DES POLITIQUES D'ÉLIMINATION TOTALE DU COVIDE EN NOUVELLE-ZÉLANDE La Première ministre néo-zélandaise Jacinda Ardern est une figure controversée de la campagne mondiale contre Covid-19, alors que son pays a imposé les mesures sanitaires les plus strictes au monde pendant l'été. Dans une vidéo en direct sur Facebook du mois d'août, Ardern a annoncé: "Nous mettons tout le monde en quarantaine. Maintenant, nous imposons également des tests. Cela fait de nous les plus stricts au monde ... nous allons un peu plus loin." (1) (2) Avec seulement 25 décès au total avec / du Covid-19 (3), tous les cas positifs au Covid-19 ont été placés dans l'une des 32 installations de quarantaine obligatoires dans le pays de 4,8 millions. column31: Provinces are entitled to differ in their response. The way our constitution is structured gives provinces the power to respond to local health matters, and the conditions in Alberta and Ontario are different. They don’t need to do the same thing. The Covid responses of the provinces don’t just need to take account of the actual case numbers - in crafting a health response it could be open to provincial governments to consider the structure of their society and even the attitudes of their citizens. A public health approach that works in Alberta may not work in Ontario and vice versa, for reasons beyond just the nature of the virus itself. That said, there are some big differences in the approaches between the two provinces. Kenney has said his approach will not be “enforcement heavy” – he has focused on voluntary measures, and said we cannot enforce our way out of a pandemic. Meanwhile, Ford has talked about ticketing and called for huge fines in some instances. And some of Ford's lockdown orders are arbitrary. For example, exempting dance studios but closing gyms. There seems to be little public health rationale for this approach. When we are talking about the constitutionality of these measures, generally a narrowly tailored approach will be easier to justify. All of these measures implicate our Charter rights, whether it is freedom of assembly, expression, association or religious freedom. Kenney’s measures look more narrowly tailored and lack the arbitrariness of some of Ford’s lockdown measures, and for that reason will be more likely to survive a legal challenge if one is brought.

column36:
Good morning everyone.  I've had a few of you reach out to me asking me for the template that I used when contacting head offices of any companies/businesses that refuse me service for not wearing a mask.  My template is a bit too big for a private message so I am posting it here for you.  I'll show you the exact email I sent to Booster Juice, Dollar Store and Tim Horton's.  All three got back to me within 24 hours and all three apologized to me.  

The key here is to do a little research and find out who the COO or CEO is in Canada.  You tell them that your human rights have been violated and you are considering legal action.  Here is the letter I wrote along with some attachments I sent. 

This is not allowing me to attach the letter from MPP Randy Hillier.  I'll see if I can add to it by picture.   But this is the EXACT letter I sent to all three CEO's and got apologies all three times.

HERE IS THE EXACT LETTER I WROTE

Dear Mr. Cil (CEO Tim Horton's Canada) 

I attempted to call your Corporate Office and was directed to this email address.  I hope I have reached the correct person as I'm trying to get in touch with Corporate Compliance. This letter is in response to a very unsettling and disturbing incident that I had at one of your stores in Brampton, Ontario Canada.  The location was on Father Tobin and Torbram Road.

I was in the process of asking for coffee and a bagel and then a different employee (presumably a manager or shift supervisor) told me that I had to wear a mask.  She demanded it.  I informed her that I have a medical exemption.  She then asked me what my condition was.  I informed her that she was not allowed to ask me that.  According to the Personal Health Information Act, you cannot ask a person what their condition is.  I felt it was best to contact you, Mr Cil, first before considering taking legal action against the business for an infringement of my Charter rights.  I'd rather avoid this course of action.  

To be sure that I was not misunderstanding her intention, I asked her again 'are you refusing to allow me into the store and also refusing to adhere to the letter of the law'? She stated again that she absolutely can ask for my medical condition.  I have the by-law on my phone which shows that there are exceptions where people do not have to wear a mask.  I asked her if she was aware of this by-law to which she replied, "I don't know what a by-law is."  
I always want to make sure that I am handling things in the right way and give employees the benefit of the doubt as I know sometimes they are not trained correctly. I asked her again her intention, she stated, yet again - she could ask for my condition, which as I'm sure you aware according to the by law...is illegal.
Below please find a copy of the Ontario Bylaw, indicating medical exemptions, religious exemptions, mental health exemptions and exemptions for children:
Some individuals may be unable to wear a mask. The Region is asking residents to be supportive to others in our community who may be exempt and remind residents every person’s situation is different. For those unable to wear a mask, the bylaw does not require them to disclose the reason for the exemption. Here are just some of the reasons why one should not be forced to wear a mask.

Children under the age of two. These very young children must not wear a face covering because of the risk of suffocation.
Individuals with a medical condition that makes it difficult to wear a mask. This can include but is not limited to:
Medical condition, mental health condition, cognitive condition or disability that prevents wearing a mask or face covering.
Medical condition that makes it difficult to breathe or someone who is unconscious or incapacitated.
People who are hearing impaired, or are communicating with a person who is hearing impaired, and where the ability to see the mouth is essential for communication.
Individuals who are unable to put on or remove a mask without assistance.

Note: Businesses are not permitted to require proof that an exemption applies.
As you can see, Businesses are NOT permitted to ask for proof of exemption. To do so is to violate the law. Additionally - People with exemptions that require accommodation in accordance with the Ontario Human Rights code must be given such accommodation or be found in violation of the Code.
Businesses must still adhere to every aspect of the Ontario Human Rights Code.  Also, on the Ontario Human Rights Commission Website under Covid Questions and Answers, under Section 13, It states "no one should be discriminated against for wanting to wear a mask of FOR NOT WANTING TO WEAR A MASK".
My rights were violated by your Father Tobin location in general, and by your employee, in particular. I am planning on going back and I do sincerely hope that your store employees and managers are educated as to the specifics of the law. My sincere hope is that your Chief Compliance Officer will respond positively (truncated)

column31: KARY MULLIS, INVENTOR OF THE PCR TEST: "IT DOESN'T TELL YOU THAT YOU'RE SICK." In 1993, Kary Mullis was awarded a Nobel Prize in chemistry for his invention of the polymerase chain reaction method, or PCR test. Its sole purpose is to make millions to billions of copies of a particular DNA sample so that it can be measurable and later studied. Mullis clearly states that PCR tests are not designed to detect if a person is infected, that is, sick, or whether a virus, like Covid-19, that is present in the body is the cause of an infection. With such clear instructions on the appropriate use of the PCR test by the inventor, why are governments misapplying it to detect Covid-19 infection and, in turn, to drive public health measures? column31: I would really like to know where the trust fund kid gets his privileged and fairness facts from!! When my family came to Canada it wasnt much of a country but more just undeveloped land.. They left their families behind and crossed an ocean.. Broke their backs (literally and metaphorically) to build this great country so they and other new comers could have a good life.. They went back to Europe to fight 2 wars (some against their own blood) in the most terrible circumstances possible with tens of millions of men, women and children (many soldiers as 15,16,17 year olds fought)dying.. Returning and enduring tough times like the 30's.. They built up the agriculture and cities that are remarkable today.. They came with zero dollars in their pockets, taking any job and many times jobs to survive.. They endured long cold winters with limited food... Men would travel great distances to provide under dangerous and bleak working conditions and when hurt (not if but when) they were tossed aside without compensation and medical treatment.. They had their children working in lumber camps and farms to help out and make ends meet.. Many lost children as the infant mortality rate was much higher than today.. Families with 14 children would be cut down to 10.. They never bitched about the way life was and kept pushing forward.. Life at that time was absolutely unfair just as it is today but they did what they had to do.. They worked hard, learned trades, got educated, lobbied for labour laws, mandatory education for all children and did everything they could possibly do to have a better life.. Not just for them but everyone.. They did the most incredible transformation of this planet so everyone would have an opportunity to have a better life.. Now ask yourself, does that sound privileged to you?? They fought wars as children and kids now days need safe places and get offended when you tell them they cant have something without earning it! They some how are entitled to everything without doing anything for it! If You were to tell your grandparents something is unfair how would they react?? My grandma would laugh at me and say "better go do something about it. Its not just going to fall into your lap". My grandpa woupd have smacked me upside the head and said "boy lifes not fair, its what you make of it". They were humble people that expected nothing in life and worked beyond hard for everything they had while still building and helping out the communities they were apart of.. If they were alive today and seen what is going on in this countrt today they would loss their minds.. They never sat idly while governments tried to bully them or new settlers tried to take advantage of them.. They would not have allowed changes to the laws and values they worked so hard to obtain.. They most certainly would not allow a government to bring in hundreds of thousands of designer jean wearing, laptop carrying "refugees" to come and not assimilate and be unproductive members of society.. They questioned anything that seemed out of their beliefs, traditions and common way of life regardless of reprisal or not.. They did whatever was needed of them no matter the physical, mental or financial costs.. There was no "Im offended because of" or "thats not fair" attitude.. No god damn safe zones and genderless b.s.! Everyday you woke up, pulled your pants up and did what you had to do.. Its been like that here in Canada for generations since!! I would like to know whatvabout that is privileged?? I feel that its a privilege for new comers now days to come to such a great place and not make the sacrifices people before them made!! The way this country is headed now is a slap in the face to those men and women that made this country what it is.. I will not sit and watch the governments of today (federal, provincal or any)destroy what was so hard worked for!! I will do everything I am capable of to make sure that those efforts were not in vain!! Its bullshit what is going on coast to coast to coast in this country and needs to be stopped!!! White middle class privilege my ass!!! Trudeau is the definition of that and for him to try and destroy what he had no hand in building is treasonous and I will not stand for it!! Dismantling freedom of speech, reliable affordable energy and kissing the worlds ass while the citizens of this nation go hungry and cold is blasphemy and needs to come to an end!! The people of Canada, white, black,green, purple or orange need to stand together to stop this undoing of what those amazing people before us left for us!! Everyone needs to do their part to make sure Canada stays the greatest country in the world bar none!!!!

column31: The NHS has been instructed to prepare for mass Covid-19 vaccination of the public from December 1 in one of the biggest immunisation drives in British history. The plans will see up to 1,500 GP practices and drive-through centres ordered to open from 8am to 8pm every day, each dispensing at least 1,000 jabs a week – meaning there will be capacity for at least one million doses to be administered weekly. Health officials said on Tuesday that the NHS would be ready to deliver the jabs as quickly as they can be supplied, with medical and nursing students and retired medics being drafted in to help. Ten million doses of Pfizer and BioNTech's vaccine are due to be delivered by the end of this year as long as regulatory approval is granted. Matt Hancock, the Health Secretary, said on Tuesday that British regulators will be able to make a judgment on the safety of the vaccine "within days" of getting a formal licence application, expected later this month. There are hopes that trial results from a vaccine being developed by Oxford University and Astra Zeneca could be released as soon as next week. Government adviser Sir John Bell said he was optimistic that Britain could "hit the new year with two or three vaccines" ready for distribution. Health officials are optimistic that vaccines could be distributed by mid-December, but the NHS has been told to be ready by the start of the month in case the green light is given sooner. NHS bosses warned GPs that "the additional workload of a Covid-19 vaccination programme may require practices to prioritise clinical activity". GPs will be paid £12.58 for each vaccine dose they or a practice nurse administers. The Royal College of GPs said doctors need "clarity on what work we should stop doing". GPs have been told they can scale back other work as the vaccination programme takes precedence. On Tuesday, the Government's daily figures showed 532 Covid-19 deaths in the UK in the previous 24 hours, up from 194 on Monday. The figure is the highest recorded since May 12 and brings total deaths in the UK to 49,770, with the toll set to top 50,000 on Wednesday. The Government's Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation (JCVI) has drawn up plans for prioritisation of the vaccines, starting with those living or working in care homes. Health officials said on Tuesday that the list of 11 categories, including everyone over the age of 50, covers the categories which made up 99 per cent of deaths in the first wave. Analysis by The Telegraph suggests that the first batch of 10 million vaccines promised by Pfizer could be used up entirely by the top two priority groups, made up of care home residents and workers, NHS staff and those over the age of 80. Experts said it could take around six months to vaccinate all the "at risk" groups if the batch of 40 million jabs was the only one on offer. There are fears that tougher restrictions could have to be extended if people use the news of the vaccine to relax their behaviour, leading to the virus's reproduction rate increasing. Fifty Conservative MPs have formed a new backbench group to fight the imposition of a third national lockdown at the beginning of next month, The Telegraph can disclose. Former Government chief whip Mark Harper and ex-Brexit minister Steve Baker are the chairman and deputy chairman of the new Covid Recovery Group, which launched on Tuesday. The group will be seen in Westminster as an echo of the European Research Group, a group of Tory MPs who were successfully whipped by Mr Baker to oppose Theresa May's Brexit deal in the last Parliament. The vaccine by Pfizer and BioNTech, which could prevent more than 90 per cent of people from getting Covid-19, is one of 11 vaccines currently in the final stages of testing. Health officials have said the programme will offer any vaccines which are found to work even if they are not all equally effective. A Government source said: "We will go with what we've got. We save most lives by doing it that way, by going with what is available in the here and now." Officials stressed that different types of vaccines may have different effectiveness in particular age groups, or other risk profiles. Because the Pfizer jab has to be stored at a temperature of minus 70C, supplies will be delivered from Belgium frozen in cases and will only be able to be kept in standard fridges for a number of days. Until now, the biggest vaccination programme delivered in the UK was 15 million flu jabs last year. This winter, the NHS is aiming to immunise 30 million people.

column31: My weekly update of the coronavirus situation in Hamilton. Hamilton has a population of 536,917 people. As of Oct 30, 128,536 tests have been completed at Assessment Centres or other facilities (long term care homes, retirement homes, other congregate settings) with 5,624 new tests in the previous 7 days. There have been 1,766 confirmed and probable cases*. Of those cases, 724 cases (41%)** had underlying health issues (diabetes, cancer, heart/renal/chronic lung disease). Only 166 cases (9%) required hospitalization, with 4 hospitalizations in the previous 7 days. 1,551 people have recovered, with 122 recoveries in the previous 7 days. There are currently 164 active cases - 1 person out of every 3,273 people living in Hamilton. There have been 48 deaths***, an average of 6.85 per month since the first death on March 24, with 0 deaths in the previous 7 days. The City doesnt list which deaths also had the aforementioned underlying health issues - all deaths could have come from the cases who had other health issues, but without specifics, it's reasonable to assume that of those deaths, 19 (41%) had diabetes, cancer, or heart/renal/lung disease. All deaths were over 40 years old: 1 death between the ages of 40-49; 7 deaths between the ages of 60-69; 6 deaths between the ages of 70-79; 26 deaths between the ages of 80-89; 7 deaths between the ages of 90-99; and 1 death aged 100 or above. There have been no deaths under the age of 40, even though, presumably, 41% of the cases under 40 years of age had one of the underlying health conditions. The average age of the deceased is 81.08 years old - the life expectancy in Canada is 82.52 years old. Hamilton's mandatory mask bylaw came into effect on Jul 20. With the virus having a 14 day incubation period, Aug 3 was the first day where any impact of the mask bylaw would be evident. There have been 135 new cases in the last 7 days, a 10% drop from the 151 cases the previous week, and a 26% drop from the 184 cases for the week ending Oct 16 (the week-over-week running 10-day total fell from 22 on Jul 17, to 15 on Jul 31 - a 31.81% drop - without mandatory masks). 98.63% of all the tests completed were negative (of the people tested, only 1.37% tested positive****), resulting in only 0.32% of the population of Hamilton ever having been infected. Only 2.4% of new tests in the previous 7 days have been positive - 97.6% of those tests have been negative. Summarized statistics for the past 7 days: 5,624 tests, 135 cases, 122 recoveries, 4 hospitalizations, 0 deaths This is all publicly available, and independently verifiable information. All numbers are drawn from the City of Hamilton's Coronavirus page, which is updated every business day. Historical data is saved each week to the internet archive for reference. https://www.hamilton.ca/coronavirus/status-cases-in-hamilton Ages of the deceased have been drawn from: https://www.thespec.com/news/hamilton-region/2020/03/31/what-you-need-to-know-about-covid-19-in-hamilton-and-halton.html?utm_source=facebook&source=the%20hamilton%20spectator&utm_medium=SocialMedia&utm_campaign=&utm_campaign_id=&utm_content= On Oct 4, the article was revised to remove all references to specific ages and instead groups the deceased into age brackets, and doesn't separate any deaths above the age of 80. The previous article listed each individual age. The URL has never been saved to the Internet Archive, but I have a PDF saved prior to the revision - should any readers wish it for their own research, I can provide it. To put the numbers in perspective, there were 331 overdose deaths in Hamilton in 2019, an average of 27.58 per month (6.89 per week/.98 per day). https://www.thespec.com/news/hamilton-region/2020/01/10/soaring-number-of-death-investigations-reveals-deadly-toll-of-hamilton-s-opioid-crisis.html It is also worth noting that on Sep 24, Ontario's Chief Coroner Dirk Huyer said during a provincial health update: “We are unfortunately seeing an incredibly increased number of deaths from drug toxicity and the number is upwards of 35 to 40 per cent higher than we’ve seen since the pandemic started, compared to last year’s numbers”. https://toronto.citynews.ca/2020/09/24/overdose-deaths-in-ontario-climb-by-up-to-40-since-pandemic-started-chief-coroner/ If the increase in Hamilton is consistent with that of the province, then there have been an average of 38.61 overdose deaths since the start of the pandemic, or an increase of 11 overdose deaths per month. The increase in average monthly deaths by overdoses alone has been greater than the deaths attributed to the virus. *As of Aug 9, the City stopped reporting confirmed and probable cases separately and have just combined them together. Previously, the City clarified the cases as 'A probable case is a symptomatic individual with travel outisde of Canada, or close contact with a known case, or close contact with a person with acute respiratory illness who has recently traveled (truncated)

These methods can only be conducted in laboratories with specialist containment facilities and are time consuming and complex.” In other words, the redefinition of “positive test” to “case” to “infection” is deliberately WRONG. It follows that any attempt to estimate the R rate, or the time taken for the number of infections to double, is bound to be WRONG. It further follows that when the proponents of Lockdown insist that it is impossible to achieve herd immunity without a vaccine, they are also WRONG. The Lockdown that is set to cause untold suffering is based on WRONG forecasts, themselves based on WRONG data and an extremely unscientific determination to ignore all evidence that contradicts the pre-determined doctrine that Lockdown is the best and only solution to Covid-19. column31: Sir Patrick Vallance and Professor Chris Whitty have been summoned before MPs to explain the "evidence and rationale" behind the second national coronavirus lockdown. The chief scientific adviser and chief medical officer will face the science and technology select committee on Tuesday afternoon amid mounting concern that the graphs shown at a press conference on Saturday evening were out of date and alarmist. Modelling presented by Sir Patrick showed that, under a worst case scenario, 4,000 deaths a day could occur by December 20. However, the forecast was compiled on October 9, five days before new three-tier restrictions came into effect, and researchers at Oxford University pointed out that, if the modelling had been correct, deaths would now stand at around 1,000 a day. The current rolling seven-day average is around 260. It has since emerged that the modelling was based on an 'R' rate of 1.3 to 1.5 and shown despite the Government publishing a rate of between 1.1 and 1.3 the day before the press conference. Committee chairman Greg Clark said: "This is an important moment in the handling of the pandemic. Parliament must have the chance to understand and question the evidence and rationale behind the new restrictions in advance of Wednesday's debate and vote. "I am grateful to Sir Patrick Vallance and Professor Chris Whitty for having agreed immediately to my request to appear before the science and technology committee on Tuesday." Last week, Sir Patrick said the three-tier restrictions were starting to have an impact and the 'R' rate was now clearly in decline. A graph shown at the press conference also illustrated a clear downward trend. Professor Tim Spector, of King's College London, said a national lockdown was being implemented just as the second wave was "running out of steam in the worst affected areas". But Professor Neil Ferguson, of Imperial College, a member of the Scientific Pandemic Influenza Group on Modelling (SPI-M) group which modelled the 4,000 deaths graph, said it showed a situation where the tiers had little impact. "The 'up to 4,000 deaths a day' scenarios represent preliminary work to generate a new reasonable worst case planning scenario to assist NHS and other Government planning," he said. "The reasonable worst case is intended to be pessimistic, so these scenarios assumed an 'R' value of 1.3 to 1.5 and that the tier system would have minimal impact. "SPI-M also generate six-week projections on a weekly basis. As Sir Patrick Vallance indicated on Saturday, the latest analyses indicate that while Tier 2 and 3 measures have reduced the rate of growth of the epidemic, the 'R' value is still above one and hospital admissions are doubling every 17 days. "Thus even allowing for the effects of the current tier system, the most recent SPI-M projections suggest that, without further action, the second wave is set to exceed the first wave in hospital demand and deaths." Prof Spector said new data from the King's app, which has been monitoring the spread since the first wave, showed that cases stopped growing in northern England four days ago.

column31: Mask confusion.. First, we were warned that the wearing of masks could cause more harm than good to members of the general public. Jenny Harries, UK deputy chief medical officer said wearing a mask could put people at more risk. Let’s remember at this time the science very clearly suggested that there was no scientific evidence that wearing masks would protect people from respiratory viruses in general community settings. This view was reflected when Dr Anthony Fauci initially told US citizens not to wear masks and a paper in the prestigious journal The New England Journal of Medicine cemented this by stating mask wearing outside of a hospital setting “…offers little, if any, protection from infection.” But then, the U-turn: we were next told we should all wear face coverings or masks, because the science had changed. But was the U-turn down to changing science or changing politics? Shouldn’t we rely on the latest science? So how’s this: a brand new study by the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention found, in a study of outpatients from 11 healthcare centres, that of those who tested positive and went on to develop Covid symptoms, 71% reported always wearing face coverings or masks (within 14 days of onset of symptoms). This contrasted with just 4% for those who reported never wearing masks, and the same proportion again who reported rarely wearing one. This obviously doesn’t take into account any differences in viral load or exposure, or the ability of a mask-wearer to reduce (or increase) transmission to others. What’s striking is that the data show that the proportion testing positive was directly and positively associated with the amount of mask wearing and that there were 18 times more Covid symptomatic/positive test people in the “always” wearers versus the “never” wearer groups. It sure puts some questions into the minds of those who might have thought masks were a good thing. Interestingly, the same relationship with mask-wearing was found with those who tested negative, who also had symptoms, presumably linked to false negatives or other respiratory pathogens. This suggests that SARS-CoV-2 transmission, at least with or without masks, works in much the same way as with other respiratory pathogens – so surely that re-validates the older science that says, don’t bother wearing masks in community settings? Given that the CDC data suggests that mask wearers may become massive reservoirs of SARS-CoV-2 and other respiratory viruses, are you still persuaded, if you wear a mask, that you'll be protecting others?
