column36:
MEDIA RELEASE | PAULINE HANSON URGES GOVERNMENT TO REJECT THE GREAT RESET

One Nation leader Pauline Hanson has warned of devastating consequences if Australia adopts the World Economic Forum’s plans for a “great reset” across the globe.

The World Economic Forum is urging a “revamp of all aspects of our societies and economies” in response to the Covid-19 recession in the areas of education, social contracts and working conditions.

“To use the pandemic as an excuse to overturn lives, push control agendas, and meddle in social systems in countries across the world is totally unacceptable,” Senator Hanson said.

“This so-called reset is absolute rubbish and we should make a stand to play no part in it, to protect Australians and our way of life.”

In a Motion to the Senate, Senator Hanson will ask the Parliament to note that adopting the policies would devastate “the economic wellbeing and individual freedoms of Australians”.

Senator Hanson’s motion also asks the Senate to vote on whether the Australian Government should boycott all World Economic Forum events in protest over the Great Reset agenda.

The World Economic Forum claimed the drastic measure is needed to counteract social and economic problems caused by Covid-19 and avoid what it claimed would be the “worst depression since the 1930s”.

“Every country, from the United States to China, must participate, and every industry, from oil and gas to tech, must be transformed. In short, we need a ‘Great Reset’ of capitalism,” the World Economic Forum says on its website.

The World Economic Forum is a non-profit foundation based in Geneva, whose members include world leaders, billionaires, business executives and celebrities. Members include Prince Charles, Al Gore, Greta Thunberg, along with senior executives of the United Nations, the European Central Bank, the OECD, the IMF, Greenpeace and WWF.

On Saturday, the New York State Bar Association passed a resolution urging the state to make it mandatory for all New Yorkers to get a COVID-19 vaccine when one becomes available — even if people object to the vaccine for religious, philosophical or personal reasons.

In May, the association — one of the nation's largest state bar groups — issued an 83-page report calling for mandatory COVID-19 vaccination for all Americans; the only exception, the association said, would be doctor-ordered medical reasons.

Acknowledging that some Americans may oppose the vaccine, the report said, "Nonetheless, for the sake of public health, mandatory vaccinations for COVID-19 should be required in the United States as soon as it is available."

According to New York vaccine rights attorney Patricia Finn, the bar association's recommendations are highly unusual. "An association for attorneys is not in the position to give medical advice and recommendations," said Finn. "Attorneys should not be making medical policies."

Leah Wilson, Stand for Health Freedom's executive director and co-founder, concurs. "No one is in the position to practice population-based medicine. Population-based medicine completely wipes out informed consent and, by proxy, infringes on human rights."

column36:
Breaking News, California: UC Regents Flu Vaccine Mandate Currently NOT in Effect, By Court Order

The University of California Board of Regents Executive Order requiring its faculty, staff, and students to be vaccinated with the flu vaccine by November 1, 2020, is no longer in effect. On November 4th, Judge Richard Seabolt will determine whether or not the UC Regents can or cannot mandate the flu vaccine.

Per lead counsel Richard Jaffe, Esq., the following is the judge’s ruling: 

“This Tentative Ruling is made by Judge Richard Seabolt Plaintiffs’ Motion for Preliminary Injunction is CONTINUED to 1:30 p.m. on November 4, 2020. The court requires additional time to review this matter.

The parties shall send courtesy copies of their papers directly to Department 521 via overnight mail no later than October 22, 2020. The parties shall comply with the form and format requirements of rule 3.1110 of the California Rules of Court.

UC shall not take adverse action against any employee or student who comes to campus who has not had a flu shot between now and when this court hears this matter. (See UC’s October 8, 2020 Opposition to Application to Reset Hearing Date in which UC committed not to do so.)”

***

We at Physicians for Informed Consent (PIC) are grateful that we have been able to help many of you with your questions about the UC Regents flu vaccine executive order. If you have more questions, please don’t hesitate to contact us through our website. 

To read a summary of the research data which explains why flu vaccine mandates are not science-based, read PIC’s letter to the UC Board of Regents here: https://physiciansforinformedconsent.org/physicians-for-informed-consent-sends-cautionary-letter-to-uc-board-of-regents-regarding-its-new-flu-shot-mandate-emphasizes-lack-of-scientific-basis/

column31: UK Government are looking to use the Mental Health Act 1983 to introduce compulsory COVID-19 vaccinations.. Discusses grounds on which a person may be detained—‘sectioned’—under the Act, and the legal basis for treatment of detained persons without consent. Mental health law permits the detention of a person for treatment for the protection of others, and permits compulsory medical treatment of a person so detained. Section 63 of the Mental Health Act 1983 permits treatment without consent to persons detained under the Act, even if they possess decision-making capacity. Given vaccine hesitancy, it may be necessary to compel vaccination in order to achieve herd immunity. The justifications for compulsory vaccination map onto the criteria for detention and treatment contained in the Mental Health Act 1983. Compulsory vaccination and human rights law compliance - We focus on the human rights enshrined in the European Convention on Human Rights (ECHR), since these rights are domestically enforceable in virtue of the Human Rights Act 1998 (HRA 1998). The UK is also a party to other international human rights law instruments, which we do not treat here. Our focus is on article 8 ECHR, which protects, inter alia, the right to private and family life,19 since this is most relevant to compulsory medical treatment. Article 8 ECHR provides: 1. Everyone has the right to respect for his private and family life […] 2. There shall be no interference by a public authority with the exercise of this right except such as is in accordance with the law and is necessary in a democratic society in the interests of national security, public safety or the economic well-being of the country, for the prevention of disorder or crime, for the protection of health or morals, or for the protection of the rights and freedoms of others. The case law of the European Court of Human Rights establishes that the provision of medical treatment without consent constitutes an interference with article 8 ECHR: ‘the imposition of medical treatment, without the consent of a mentally competent adult patient, would interfere with a person's physical integrity in a manner capable of engaging the rights protected under Article 8(1) of the Convention’. Their conclusion: The law permits compulsory interference with bodily integrity under mental health law. This derogation from the common law principle of no treatment without consent is compatible with the ECHR. It is arguable that if compulsory treatment under mental health law is compatible with human rights law, so too is compulsory vaccination.

column35: The Covid-19 Numbers Game: The "Second Wave" is Based on Fake Statistics - Global Research
column36: "Red zones", travel bans, quarantines, "red lists". A "Second Wave". Millions of people are lining up for Covid-19 testing. The "Numbers Game". How statistics and "estimates" are used by politicians to justify the closure of the national economy and the derogation of fundamental civil rights.

COVID-19 INCREASED ALL CAUSES OF DEATH BY 1% FROM JAN-JULY 2020 VS. JAN-JULY 2019

Canada's epidemiological data for Covid-19 stands on shaky and unprecedented ground:

1) The PCR test is falsely detecting positive cases at a high rate because it is exaggerating the actual quantity of Covid-19 virus that a person may have, that is, people with barely any virus are being identified as positive cases. (1)

2) The W.H.O. has recommended that any person diagnosed with Covid-19 will automatically be marked a Covid-19 death, even though the cause of death may actually have been caused by a pre-existing condition or other cause, like heart attack. (2) (This is medically incorrect and has never been done with another disease.)

For these reasons, a more accurate picture of Covid-19 deaths may be found by comparing all cause deaths, that is, the total number of deaths caused by all diseases and events, like cancer, heart disease and accidents, from one time period to another. 

Using Statistics Canada's customizable data tool reveals that all cause deaths from January – July 2020 were only 1% more than the previous year’s period of January – July 2019, or 4,160 deaths. (3) This number thankfully does not come close to the dire projections of the Public Health Agency of Canada (PHAC), who predicted up to 44,000 Covid-19 deaths under “strong epidemic controls”. (4)

With an unreliable PCR test and the generous coding of Covid-19 deaths, is the severity of Covid-19 supported by the all cause deaths data?

(1) https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/29/health/coronavirus-testing.html 
(2) https://www.680news.com/2020/06/23/toronto-child-under-9-dies-with-covid-19-but-not-as-a-result-of-the-virus/?fbclid=IwAR07c3bMB73dfC9l9ClhGLGxCc-cwu3UqIih6URImxgKo3eKlkcgOKCBkc0
(3) https://www150.statcan.gc.ca/t1/tbl1/en/cv.action?pid=1310078501 
(4) https://www.canada.ca/content/dam/phac-aspc/documents/services/diseases/2019-novel-coronavirus-infection/using-data-modelling-inform-eng-04-28.pdf 

---------------------------------

COVID-19 AUGMENTE TOUTES LES CAUSES DE MORT DE 1% DE JAN-JUILLET 2020 VS. JAN-JUILLET 2019

Les données épidémiologiques du Canada sur Covid-19 reposent sur un terrain instable et sans précédent:

1) Le test PCR détecte faussement les cas positifs à un taux élevé car il exagère la quantité réelle de virus Covid-19 qu'une personne peut avoir, c'est-à-dire que les personnes avec à peine aucun virus sont identifiées comme des cas positifs. (1)

2) L'OMS a recommandé que toute personne diagnostiquée avec Covid-19 soit automatiquement marquée comme un décès Covid-19, même si la cause du décès peut en fait avoir été causée par une maladie préexistante ou une autre cause, comme une crise cardiaque. (2) (Ceci est médicalement fautif et n'a jamais été fait avec une autre maladie.)

Pour ces raisons, une image plus précise des décès liés au Covid-19 peut être trouvée en comparant toutes les causes de décès, c'est-à-dire le nombre total de décès causés par toutes les maladies et tous les événements, comme le cancer, les maladies cardiaques et les accidents, d'une période à l'autre.

L'utilisation de l'outil de données personnalisable de Statistique Canada révèle que toutes les causes de décès de janvier à juillet 2020 n'étaient que de 1% de plus que la période de janvier à juillet 2019 de l'année précédente, soit 4 160 décès. (3) Heureusement, ce nombre ne se rapproche pas des terribles projections de l'Agence de la santé publique du Canada (ASPC), qui a prédit jusqu'à 44 000 décès liés à Covid-19 sous «un contrôle épidémique rigoureux». (4)

Avec un test PCR peu fiable et le codage généreux des décès du Covid-19, la gravité du Covid-19 est-elle étayée par les données sur les décès toutes causes?

column36:
Nanoparticles for nasal vaccination
Abstract
The great interest in mucosal vaccine delivery arises from the fact that mucosal surfaces represent the major site of entry for many pathogens. Among other mucosal sites, nasal delivery is especially attractive for immunization, as the nasal epithelium is characterized by relatively high permeability, low enzymatic activity and by the presence of an important number of immunocompetent cells. In addition to these advantageous characteristics, the nasal route could offer simplified and more cost-effective protocols for vaccination with improved patient compliance.

The use of nanocarriers provides a suitable way for the nasal delivery of antigenic molecules. Besides improved protection and facilitated transport of the antigen, nanoparticulate delivery systems could also provide more effective antigen recognition by immune cells. These represent key factors in the optimal processing and presentation of the antigen, and therefore in the subsequent development of a suitable immune response. In this sense, the design of optimized vaccine nanocarriers offers a promising way for nasal mucosal vaccination.

column36:
To embrace freedom we must escape binary thinking.

This broadcast is a lesson to myself as much as it is to others. 

It’s time to stop fighting and start listening; all people want is to feel acknowledged, heard and understood. 

It’s called empathy. 

Empathy does not require you to agree or accept other people’s viewpoints, but it requires you to hear them and acknowledge them. 

Our failure as a human race to practice basic empathy is what is expanding the divide right now and it’s nobodies fault but our own.

By learning other points of view we can develop a greater understanding of the whole, even if doing so does not alter our own conclusions or innate biases. 

We live in a rapidly and ever changing dynamic world, therefore what we understand or believe to be true today, may not be true tomorrow. 

If we shut ourselves off or deny other points of view and judge others for seeing the world differently to ourselves, we not only close our minds to new possibilities but we expand the divide and become part of the problem, rather than the solution. 

As the great Dr Stephen Covey said, seek first to understand, before being understood. 

To be truly open minded is exceptionally hard, we become attached to our beliefs and perspectives which form our unique map of the world and our identity. 

However, we are not our thoughts. We are simply vibrational beings in human form and it is the very attachment to our own ego that keeps us trapped in cycles of boom and bust, love and hate, peace and war. 

It’s time to break the cycle by opening up and listening with love and without judgement. 

This is an evolution in consciousness and it’s at the heart of creating the change we wish to see in the world. 

Free yourself by freeing your mind, relinquish the ego and forgo the need to be right. 

If we are to make the next decade the most profound period of positive change in human history, we have to stop blaming others for our problems and begin taking personal responsibility for embracing humanity in all of its glory.

column36:
Vatican Control Of The World Health Organization Population Policy - An Interview With Milton P. Siegel | Assistant Director-General

[Via The Archives Of WHO]: Milton P. Siegel was born in 1911 in Des Moines in the United States of America. He joined WHO in 1948, as Director of the Division of Administration and Finance, from where he moved on to become Assistant Director-General until 1973. He died in 1995 in Houston.

https://www.who.int/archives/fonds_collections/special/oral_history_siegel/en/

This interview with Professor Milton P. Siegel, who for 24 years was the Assistant Director General of the World Health Organization, was recorded in 1992 by Dr. Stephen D. Mumford, President of the Center for Research on Population and Security. This is the first time that it has been made available to the public. Because of his position and the length of his tenure, Professor Siegel is considered among the world's foremost authorities on the development of World Health Organization policy. In this interview, he reveals the influence of the Vatican in shaping WHO policy, particularly in blocking adoption of the concept that overpopulation is a grave public-health threat -- a concept which, in WHO's early years, enjoyed a broad consensus among member countries. Without this separation of population dynamics from WHO public-health policy, the Vatican would have found it much more difficult to subsequently manipulate governments on such issues as family planning and abortion. National leaders would have been able to refer to the international consensus, as demonstrated by WHO policy. WHO, they could have insisted, has determined that family planning and abortion -- like clean water, good nutrition, and immunizations -- are necessary to protect public health. Professor Siegel decided to speak out on the subject. As he was involved in the WHO at an early stage, his personal experience provides ample evidence that the Vatican influenced WHO policy development from the outset, during the early period of the Interim Commission in 1946. In its 63-year history, this international health body has had a deplorable record in family planning. Its commitment has been minuscule, and even today family planning accounts for only a tiny fraction of its budget. Professor Siegel joined the World Health Organization in 1946, when it was still in its formative stages -- under the umbrella of the United Nations, created just the year before. Because of his earlier work in North America and the Middle East, he was asked, in effect, to be one of WHO's "founding fathers". So he came on board on the senior staff of the Interim Commission. Dr. Brock Chisholm of Canada was the Executive Director of the Commission, which set up the permanent organization with headquarters in Geneva, Switzerland. Dr. Chisholm was chosen to be WHO's first Director General.

Dear Honorable Cameron Friesen, 

I am pleased you recently questioned the motives of a group of 200 Manitoba Medical doctors who signed a petition criticizing your COVID response measures and suggesting that they be enhanced.  

 I trust you are aware that some 45+ thousand Medical scientists & MD’s lead by 3 of the world’s leading Scientists/Epidemiologists recommending an end to lockdowns and rather move to a “Focused Protection” of our elderly and immune compromised.   

IF NOT, Please read The Great Barrington Declaration   www.gbdeclaration.org   

I am also writing this letter in the hope of gaining some clarity regarding your decision making which has led to province-wide pandemic, panic and chaos.  These policies are not in line with rapidly developing scientific data indicating greater harm is being done to our physical and mental health as well to our short and long-term economic situation.  

In the beginning, we were all instructed that two weeks to “flatten the curve” would keep the health system from being overwhelmed. At the time we had little information on “SARS CoV2” virus, how it was transmitted nor its potential severity.  We were happy to consent and “do our part”.  Soon it became very apparent that the overwhelming of the hospital system was not occurring.   

Presently, in Manitoba, many physicians are silently questioning the appropriateness of public health policies. They dare not speak out publicly fearing retribution from their licensing boards. How sad! 

Mounting Epidemiological evidence clearly shows that a real pandemic never manifested after all.  This irrefutable evidence has been available for at least 4-5 months, yet in spite of the substantial research, your offices are continuing with the same old narrative of things are getting worse.  This false story is being used to justify draconian public health policies that are proving to have very little health benefits but rather contributing to considerable mental and physical harm to our children and adults.  This is especially evident in our poorest and most vulnerable sectors.   

You are aware that Sweden took a very different approach than much of the world, and as of mid-September, their infection rate reached an all-time low, and covid related deaths were at essentially zero.    However, in 22 of 31 European countries which enacted strict lockdowns, we witnessed higher infection rates and more deaths.  

Sweden has also saved their country from financial and economic ruin and are free from the mental health issues being experienced in most other countries worldwide. 

It is very interesting to note that incidents of the “seasonal flu” have all but disappeared this year! Less than 10 are reported so far.  How is that possible?   

Dr. Lawrence Rosenberg, Montreal’s medical officer, has stated “this Covid virus is much like the seasonal flu”.  A group of over 400 Belgian doctors have stated “Covid 19 is not a killer virus, but a treatable condition”. 

Eighteen Canadian doctors wrote the Ontario Premier saying, “your policies risk significantly harming our children with lifelong consequences”. We now see in Manitoba the same kind of policies being put forward to us. 

Following an Influenza pandemic in 2011, a review of the literature by the British Columbia Centers for Disease Control that sought to evaluate the effectiveness of social distancing measures such as school closures, travel restrictions, and limitations on mass gatherings as a means to address such pandemic concluded that “such drastic restrictions are not economically feasible and are predicted to delay viral spread, but not impact overall mortality”.

OPEN LETTER from a medical doctor to BC Minister of Health

Stephen Malthouse, MD
Denman Island, BC V0R 1T0
Email: scmalthouse@zohomail.com
October 2020

Dr. Bonnie Henry,
British Columbia Provincial Health Officer,
Ministry of Health,
1515 Blanshard Street,
Victoria, BC V8W 3C9

Dear Dr. Henry,
I am a physician who has been in family medical practice in BC for more than 40 years and a member of the College of Physicians and Surgeons of BC since 1978.
I am writing this letter with the hope that you will be able to clarify the basis of your decision-making that has led our provincial government, health ministry, regional health officers, hospitals, medical staff, WorkSafe BC, businesses, and everyday citizens to follow pandemic policies that do not appear based on high-quality scientific research and, in fact, appear to be doing everyone a great deal of harm.1
The early intent of mitigation measures to “flatten the curve”, when we knew very little about SARS-CoV-2, its mode of transmission, and the severity of COVID-19, was reasonable. I believe that most physicians in Canada, myself included, whether active or retired, prepared themselves to take part on the front lines for the expected COVID-19 tsunami. Very soon it was apparent that the expected overwhelming of the hospital system was not going to occur, and now BC physicians have questions about the appropriateness of your public health policies.
The epidemiological evidence clearly shows that the “pandemic” is over and no second wave will follow. The evidence has been available for at least 4-5 months and is irrefutable.2-4 
Yet, in spite of this substantial body of research, your office is perpetuating the narrative that a pandemic still exists and a second wave is expected. This false story is being used to justify public health policies that appear to have no health benefits, have already caused considerable harm, and threaten to create more harm in the future.
As you are aware, Sweden took an entirely different approach and, as of mid-September, their infection rate reached an all-time low and Covid-19 related deaths were at zero; 22 of 31 European countries, most of which enacted strict lockdowns, had higher infection rates. Sweden has also largely escaped the financial ruin and catastrophic mental health problems experienced in other countries, including Canada and the U.S.A.
Dr. Lawrence Rosenberg, Montréal’s medical officer, has stated “this COVID virus is much like the seasonal flu”. A group of over 400 Belgian doctors have stated “COVID is not a killer virus, but a treatable condition”. Eighteen Canadian doctors wrote the Ontario Premier,
Doug Ford, stating “your policies risk significantly harming our children with lifelong consequences”. The Ontario policies are very similar to those of British Columbia.
In 2011, a review of the literature by the British Columbia Centres for Disease Control that sought to evaluate the effectiveness of social distancing measures such as school closures, travel restrictions, and limitations on mass gatherings as a means to address an influenza pandemic concluded that “such drastic restrictions are not economically feasible and are predicted to delay viral spread, but not impact overall mortality”. [Italics added]
Specifically, there appears to be no scientific or medical evidence for  5-6
1. Self-isolation of asymptomatic people
2. social distancing
3. facemasks
4. arbitrary closure of businesses
5. closure of schools, daycares, park amenities, and playgrounds
6. the discontinuance of access to education, medical, dental, chiropractic, naturopathic, hearing, dietary, therapeutic, and other support for the physically and mentally disabled, particularly special needs children with neurological disorders
7. the closing down of or restrictions on religious places of worship.
According to the CDC Pandemic Severity Index, none of these measures have been warranted. 
The Great Barrington Declaration, signed by more than 30,000 health scientists and medical doctors from around the world, adds support for this statement.
Surprisingly, the recommendation for reducing COVID-19 morbidity and mortality by supplementing with vitamin D, a measure that is supported by high-quality research, has been absent from your frequent public broadcasts and professional bulletins.7 
Optimizing nutrition is a convenient, inexpensive, and safe method of improving immune resistance and has been confirmed through numerous studies for both prevention and treatment of COVID-19. As far as I am aware, you have never mentioned something as simple as vitamin D supplements for our most vulnerable citizens. Yet, it was the promise to protect these same citizens that was used to justify the lockdown of a healthy population and the closure of businesses.
Why are you still using PCR testing? The Deputy Chief Medical Officer for Health in Ontario has publicly stated that the PCR test yields over 50% false (truncated)

Hi Anna,
Really enjoying all your videos, interviews and impartial journalism. It’s very refreshing and a very valuable and much needed service in these very questionable times.
I want to recount an experience I had last night 31 October, when a friend of mine (aged 67) was taken to hospital because of a heart attack. She sadly later died later in A&E.
Her ‘sister’ (aka a very, very close friend) of my friend called me about 30 minutes after the initial heart attack had happened, about 8.30 pm, distraught.
My friend’s son was with my friend when she fell ill fortunately but, unable to wake her up (she had also smashed her head through a glass table), had called an ambulance.
Her daughter managed to get to her mother’s house as the ambulance arrived and the paramedics tried to resuscitate her. They managed to get her breathing but, wouldn’t let her daughter travel with her to the hospital, something, understandably, she really wanted to do.
Instead, my friend’s daughter was told to wait at home for updates. You can imagine how agonising that was. Mother and daughter were very close, calling each other 3 – 4 times a day and seeing each other nearly every day too.
After about an hour, my friend’s ‘sister’, who doesn’t have any transport, couldn’t take the wait any more and unable to contact my friend’s daughter, I offered to take her to A&E, The Royal Free Hospital in Hampstead, North London, a major teaching hospital with 24 hour A&E facilities.
By then we knew it was too late and my friend had passed.
We probably arrived at the hospital around 10.30 pm and as with most hospitals in London, would normally expect it to be very busy, particularly given it was Halloween and a Saturday night.
Instead, as you can see from the attached photo (which I took surreptitiously because I was so surprised), A&E was empty and not a Covid patient in sight!
What was also bad is that despite having a children's emergency dept, they even refused to look at an 8 year old who was suffering with ear ache, saying they could give him pain killers (without a diagnosis?) and he’d have to go to another hospital, the Whittington in the Archway, some distance by London Transport! We cannot assume everyone can afford a cab in these difficult times and I’m not sure if they had a car.
By the time we reached the hospital around 10.30 pm my friend’s daughter had managed to get to see her mother and say her final goodbye.
There was probably about 30 minutes or so between my friend’s daughter leaving and us arriving at A&E, a very short space of time, in hospital terms.
At first we were told they couldn’t find my friend, distressing enough as that was and then when they eventually did locate her she had already been moved to the morgue.  We were then told it was no longer possible, because of Covid, for anyone to visit their deceased loved ones in the morgue??
Apart from obviously noticing how quiet the hospital was, it was also noted how quickly she was removed.
When my own mother died in the Whittington hospital (another very busy hospital) a few years ago, it took approximately four hours before she was removed (I know because I was with her and waited) and I was able to see her in the morgue the following day.
It doesn’t take much to imagine, being prevented from seeing your immediate family (or friends) following their death, is extremely sad, distressing and tragic for families and friends and, in my and increasingly more people's views, for no apparent reason?
This suggests to me, not only are the NHS Hospitals not overrun to the extent many of us are being led to believe but, also it seems there is an active policy (?) to ‘save’ the NHS by reducing services, not treating people (more people are too fearful to go & dying at home) & not spending any money on it.  I am increasingly of the view this is the reality and, I believe, what they're not really telling us.
What is also very apparent at the moment, in North London, at least, if this Saturday was anything to go by (which should have been pretty busy), there's no one on the streets after 10 pm, the roads are empty. This is without the full Lockdown!
So, my question is, if this is such a pandemic, apart from no one's catching it (we can’t even be sure it is COVID and not a mutated form of flu?), why are there no ambulances chasing around anywhere or people falling around sick, coughing & sputtering like some sort of plague?  It’s all eerily quiet, like Christmas or just after it’s snowed.
How few, including MPs within the Conservative party and the opposition (my own, Catherine West included) and MSM Journalists, don’t question any of this is beyond me?  I know this is an area of grave concern for you too.

column36:
My inbox is blowing up with constituents concerned about the integrity of elections across the country and including our state.
Here is a short video clip from the July Special Session in the CT General Assembly since it is quite topical.
I serve as the Senate Ranking Republican member of the Government Administration & Elections committee - which basically means I am the leading voice of the opposition to all the harm done to our election process in our state in recent years.
I could make a long list of terrible policies enacted on party lines in our legislature over the last decade that have undermined the integrity of our elections - from the initial registration process for voters, to the counting of ballots, to the oversight of elections and candidates, and more.
Nothing has been more harmful than the mass mailing of absentee ballot applications by our Secretary of State to every name on the voter registration rolls - with complete knowledge and utter disregard for how alarmingly inaccurate and unreliable they are.
I have called this action taken by our Secretary of State with the consent and authorization of our Governor by executive order - in direct contradiction to their constitutional and statutory limitations - a criminal act.
We are watching the affect of similar policies all across the country and you can be certain that Connecticut's election, while not likely to factor in the electoral contest for President, is no less impacted.
This clip is a small part of my remarks on the Senate floor during our debate on the bill that allowed COVID-19 to become a legitimate reason for voting absentee - a bill almost unanimously supported by members of both parties.  Expanding absentee voting (BY REQUEST) to those affected by COVID-19 was and is good policy.   That is a whole different ball game than this mass-mailing scheme.
Here I am attempting to amend our laws to prohibit such a mass mailing and restore sanity to our election process.  Unfortunately, every Democrat Senator voted against my amendment.
The results are inexplicable and emblematical of what is happening on the national stage.  If anyone reading this is skilled with analyzing data and is so inclined, I strongly urge you to investigate the election results statewide and report anomalies publicly and also share them with me.

Connecticut Secretary of the State
Election Night Reporting"

column36:
The Cautious Optimism Correspondent for Left Coast Affairs and Other Inexplicable Phenomena confesses to stirring up quite a discussion last Friday when he suggested that Joe Biden’s miraculous post-Election Night erasure of Donald Trump’s sizable leads in four critical battleground states may have been a little too miraculous.

The huge comeback was credited to record numbers of mail-in ballots that were still being counted after hours, a phenomenon that, if valid, should have occurred in just about every other state too since fears of Covid and social distancing are prevalent everywhere, not just in Wisconsin, Michigan, Pennsylvania, and Georgia.

As before, the four states where Biden enjoyed the largest gains after polls closed--three of them colossal (see chart)--happened to not only all be states he trailed in, but also the very four he needed to save any chance of winning as the window of opportunity had almost closed on him.

Based on the 33 states that mandate waiting until Election Day/Night to begin counting absentee and mail-in ballots, the odds of the four best-performing randomly matching the exact four Biden needed to win are 40,920 to 1.

Therefore such a miracle is not scheduled to occur again in a U.S. presidential election until the year 165,700 A.D. That’s U.S. history beginning in 1776 elapsing another 679 times before this should happen again.

The Correspondent’s friends “shared” the original story and sparked many heated debates elsewhere across Facebook with some skeptical commenters demanding more states and more data.

So Cautious Rockers get first dibs at the exclusive research available at CO Nation. Please enjoy the chart before it's fact-checked out of existence.

Note again that the four states where Biden enjoyed the largest—in three cases absolutely massive—improvement in vote percentages against Donald Trump just happened to be the very four that:

1) Remained uncalled, and...

2) Had 10 or more electoral votes at stake, and…

3) Were already long anticipated to be critical battleground states, and...

4) He trailed Donald Trump in (all four, plus NC), and most importantly…

5) He critically needed to win since Donald Trump was performing far better than polls had predicted and the window to salvage a victory was nearly closed.

ps. Note also how many points Biden needed in each state and how many he got.

WI: Needed 4.9. Got 5.6.

GA: Needed 8.9. Got 9.0.

MI: Needed 10.6. Got 13.3 (the only "not a squeaker" rebound)

PA: Needed [an incredible] 14.4. Got an even more incredible 15.0.

[End of main article. Readers who wish to know more about the source data read on]

I. Here is an example of how a state’s change in margin is calculated:

VIRGINIA: At the point that NBC News had both called a winner and the percentage of precincts in exceeded 75%, Joe Biden held 52.4% of votes and Donald Trump held 46.0%, a lead of 6.4 percentage points.

On Saturday, November 7th, after the bulk of absentee and mail-in ballots had been added to count totals, Joe Biden held 54.0% of votes and Donald Trump held 44.5%, a lead of 9.5 percentage points.

Thus Biden added to his margin of victory and gained 3.1 points (9.5 – 6.4 = 3.1)

OHIO: At the point that NBC News had both called a winner and the percentage of precincts in exceeded 75%, Joe Biden held 45.2% of votes and Donald Trump held 53.3%, a deficit of 8.1 percentage points.

On Saturday, November 7th, after the bulk of absentee and mail-in ballots had been added to count totals, Joe Biden held 45.2% of votes and Donald Trump held 53.4%, a deficit of 8.2 percentage points.

Thus Biden’s margin of defeat worsened and he lost another 0.1 points (8.1 – 8.2 = -0.1)

(It’s worth noting that Ohio was a major battleground state where a large number of mail-in ballots, largely Democratic, were expected and received)

II. Source data:

The Correspondent spent many hours combing through Election Night video from NBC News to find leading or trailing margins of every state that was called and then recorded data when the percent of precincts in exceeded 75%. Using vote percentages with only 2% of precincts reporting was unreliable and could lead to wild changes in margins leading to November 7th.

Then the Correspondent compared the leading or training margins on Saturday, November 7th when AP called the election for Biden and calculated the difference.

For the five critical states that remained uncalled (WI, MI, PA, GA, NC) the Correspondent noted the vote percentages for each candidate at 12AM ending Election Night.

Although he has data for NC, AZ, and NV, those three states permitted counting absentee and mail-in ballots prior to Election Day/Night and therefore don’t appear in the chart. Also, as of this posting North Carolina totals have not changed since late Election Night.

A few states had not yet reached 75% precincts in by the time the NBC livestream ended late ag night. Therefore the (truncated)

Bad news first. There will NOT be a gathering held on Friday the 6th. 

Simply put, further negotiations and preparation is needed to make this worth our while and there’s no way I can get behind something that isn’t sitting right in my gut.

It kills me this is the case, but the time constraints are too much to make sure this goes right and so with these doubts, we’ll be going to postpone it, for the time being.

I’m going to continue discussions with this business owner, who IS on board... I can say that for sure. 

I have also been in contact with a few others as well so, let me keep digging on this and will give further updates as they come in. 

My biggest worry, is not providing a functional and feasible location for our type of gathering. With more time to plan everything out, I don’t see why it’s not going to happen. 

It’s been incredible to see how many people have shown interest and how many others wish to help, speak and spread the word. 

I’m telling you...

We’re going to get our chance to be heard. It just won’t be tomorrow.

Keep an eye out over the next week as I’ll be further updating the situation. 

In the meantime, let’s keep building this community. The more this goes on, the more people I talk to that are sick of it and ready to mobilize for an event like this. 

Election stress aside, our future is bright.

California Election Day Registration

Same Day Registration and Election Day Registration

California has Same Day Registration and Election Day Registration. You can register and vote during the early voting period and on Election Day.

Where to go:
Go to your designated voting location. Click here to find where to vote.

What to bring:
Bring your California driver's license or state ID card with you. If you don't have one, bring an acceptable document with your name and current address. Acceptable documents include a recent utility bill, bank statement, or paycheck.

Need help?
Contact your Local Election Office if you have questions.

Notes:
Same day registration starts 14 days before an election and runs through Election Day.

Puncture Wounds
What Is a Puncture Wound?
Puncture wounds are not the same as cuts. A puncture wound has a small entry hole caused by a pointed object, such as a nail that you’ve stepped on. In contrast, a cut is an open wound that produces a long tear in the skin. Puncture wounds require different treatment from cuts because these small holes in the skin can disguise serious injury.

column31: My weekly summary of the coronavirus situation in Hamilton. Hamilton has a population of 536,917 people. As of Nov 6, 135,013 tests have been completed at Assessment Centres or other facilities (long term care homes, retirement homes, other congregate settings) with 6,479 new tests in the previous 7 days. There have been 1,999 confirmed and probable cases*. Of those cases, 819 cases (41%)** had underlying health issues (diabetes, cancer, heart/renal/chronic lung disease). Only 169 cases (9%) required hospitalization, with 3 hospitalizations in the previous 7 days. 1,695 people have recovered, with 144 recoveries in the previous 7 days. There are currently 251 active cases - 1 person out of every 2,139 people living in Hamilton. There have been 51 deaths***, an average of 7.28 per month since the first death on March 24, with 3 deaths in the previous 7 days (all were from the same LTC residence). The City doesnt list which deaths also had the aforementioned underlying health issues - all deaths could have come from the cases who had other health issues, but without specifics, it's reasonable to assume that of those deaths, 20 (41%) had diabetes, cancer, or heart/renal/lung disease. All deaths were over 40 years old: 1 death between the ages of 40-49; 7 deaths between the ages of 60-69; 7 deaths between the ages of 70-79; 27 deaths between the ages of 80-89; 7 deaths between the ages of 90-99; and 2 deaths aged 100 or above. There have been no deaths under the age of 40, even though, presumably, 41% of the cases under 40 years of age had one of the underlying health conditions. The average age of the deceased is 81.51 years old - the life expectancy in Canada is 82.52 years old. Hamilton's mandatory mask bylaw came into effect on Jul 20. With the virus having a 14 day incubation period, Aug 3 was the first day where any impact of the mask bylaw would be evident. There have been 233 new cases in the last 7 days (the week-over-week running 10-day total fell from 22 on Jul 17, to 15 on Jul 31 - a 31.81% drop - without mandatory masks). 98.52% of all the tests completed were negative (of the people tested, only 1.48% tested positive****), resulting in only 0.37% of the population of Hamilton ever having been infected. Only 3.59% of new tests in the previous 7 days have been positive - 96.41% of those tests have been negative. Summarized statistics for the past 7 days: 6,479 tests, 233 cases, 144 recoveries, 3 hospitalizations, 3 deaths This is all publicly available, and independently verifiable information. All numbers are drawn from the City of Hamilton's Coronavirus page, which is updated every business day. Historical data is saved each week to the internet archive for reference. https://www.hamilton.ca/coronavirus/status-cases-in-hamilton Ages of the deceased have been drawn from: https://www.thespec.com/news/hamilton-region/2020/03/31/what-you-need-to-know-about-covid-19-in-hamilton-and-halton.html?utm_source=facebook&source=the%20hamilton%20spectator&utm_medium=SocialMedia&utm_campaign=&utm_campaign_id=&utm_content= On Oct 4, the article was revised to remove all references to specific ages and instead groups the deceased into age brackets, and doesn't separate any deaths above the age of 80. The previous article listed each individual age. The URL has never been saved to the Internet Archive, but I have a PDF saved prior to the revision - should any readers wish it for their own research, I can provide it. To put the numbers in perspective, there were 331 overdose deaths in Hamilton in 2019, an average of 27.58 per month (6.89 per week/.98 per day). https://www.thespec.com/news/hamilton-region/2020/01/10/soaring-number-of-death-investigations-reveals-deadly-toll-of-hamilton-s-opioid-crisis.html It is also worth noting that on Sep 24, Ontario's Chief Coroner Dirk Huyer said during a provincial health update: “We are unfortunately seeing an incredibly increased number of deaths from drug toxicity and the number is upwards of 35 to 40 per cent higher than we’ve seen since the pandemic started, compared to last year’s numbers”. https://toronto.citynews.ca/2020/09/24/overdose-deaths-in-ontario-climb-by-up-to-40-since-pandemic-started-chief-coroner/ If the increase in Hamilton is consistent with that of the province, then there have been an average of 38.61 overdose deaths since the start of the pandemic, or an increase of 11 overdose deaths per month. The increase in average monthly deaths by overdoses alone has been greater than the deaths attributed to the virus. *As of Aug 9, the City stopped reporting confirmed and probable cases separately and have just combined them together. Previously, the City clarified the cases as 'A probable case is a symptomatic individual with travel outisde of Canada, or close contact with a known case, or close contact with a person with acute respiratory illness who has recently traveled outside of Canada and for whom laboratory results are not available, (truncated)

An online survey looking for opinions on the idea went live on the province’s website Tuesday morning. But the plan to wait for feedback faced criticism from some social media who wondered why the government wouldn’t just follow advice from public health experts and put a curfew in place if it’s needed. Winnipeg Mayor Brian Bowman was among those urging the province to implement the curfew quickly. “If the province feels this is the right thing to do, I would encourage them to just do it and not wait another day for a survey,” Bowman said Monday. “The virus doesn’t take a night off. It’s in our community right now, and if the epidemiology and the evidence would support a curfew, then I think the province should simply introduce that measure in a timely fashion and not wait for a survey.”

So interesting. 👀

Joe Biden's Twitter account got a sizable boost beginning in August from tens of thousands of fake followers purchased on the open market from troll farms in rural India, an investigation has found.

Within two weeks of Biden selecting Kamala Harris as his running mate on August 12, his Twitter following jumped by 738,595 new followers—a 9.1 percent leap. The number hit 11 million by the third week of October.

A close examination has revealed unusual patterns. A large number of Twitter accounts that followed Biden's appear to have been created exclusively for that purpose. And a large number of the users are located in small towns in rural India—in places where English-speakers are rare, and from handles run by people who don't speak English as their first language, nor appear to be genuinely invested in American politics.

OPEN LETTER

Stephen Malthouse, MD
Denman Island, BC V0R 1T0

October 2020

Dr. Bonnie Henry,
British Columbia Provincial Health Officer,
Ministry of Health,
1515 Blanshard Street,
Victoria, BC V8W 3C9

Dear Dr. Henry,

I am a physician who has been in family medical practice in BC for more than 40 years and a member of the College of Physicians and Surgeons of BC since 1978.

I am writing this letter with the hope that you will be able to clarify the basis of your decision-making that has led our provincial government, health ministry, regional health officers, hospitals, medical staff, WorkSafe BC, businesses, and everyday citizens to follow pandemic policies that do not appear based on high-quality scientific research and, in fact, appear to be doing everyone a great deal of harm.1

The early intent of mitigation measures to “flatten the curve”, when we knew very little about SARS-CoV-2, its mode of transmission, and the severity of COVID-19, was reasonable. I believe that most physicians in Canada, myself included, whether active or retired, prepared themselves to take part on the front lines for the expected COVID-19 tsunami. Very soon it was apparent that the expected overwhelming of the hospital system was not going to occur, and now BC physicians have questions about the appropriateness of your public health policies.

The epidemiological evidence clearly shows that the “pandemic” is over and no second wave will follow. The evidence has been available for at least 4-5 months and is irrefutable.2-4 Yet, in spite of this substantial body of research, your office is perpetuating the narrative that a pandemic still exists and a second wave is expected. This false story is being used to justify public health policies that appear to have no health benefits, have already caused considerable harm, and threaten to create more harm in the future.

As you are aware, Sweden took an entirely different approach and, as of mid-September, their infection rate reached an all-time low and Covid-19 related deaths were at zero; 22 of 31 European countries, most of which enacted strict lockdowns, had higher infection rates. Sweden has also largely escaped the financial ruin and catastrophic mental health problems experienced in other countries, including Canada and the U.S.A.

Dr. Lawrence Rosenberg, Montréal’s medical officer, has stated “this COVID virus is much like the seasonal flu”. A group of over 400 Belgian doctors have stated “COVID is not a killer virus, but a treatable condition”. Eighteen Canadian doctors wrote the Ontario Premier, Doug Ford, stating “your policies risk significantly harming our children with lifelong consequences”. The Ontario policies are very similar to those of British Columbia.

In 2011, a review of the literature by the British Columbia Centres for Disease Control that sought to evaluate the effectiveness of social distancing measures such as school closures, travel restrictions, and limitations on mass gatherings as a means to address an influenza pandemic concluded that “such drastic restrictions are not economically feasible and are predicted to delay viral spread, but not impact overall mortality”. [Italics added]

Specifically, there appears to be no scientific or medical evidence for5-6

    Self-isolation of asymptomatic people
    social distancing
    facemasks
    arbitrary closure of businesses
    closure of schools, daycares, park amenities, and playgrounds
    the discontinuance of access to education, medical, dental, chiropractic, naturopathic, hearing, dietary, therapeutic, and other support for the physically and mentally disabled, particularly special needs children with neurological disorders
    the closing down of or restrictions on religious places of worship.

According to the CDC Pandemic Severity Index, none of these measures have been warranted. The Great Barrington Declaration, signed by more than 30,000 health scientists and medical doctors from around the world, adds support for this statement.

Surprisingly, the recommendation for reducing COVID-19 morbidity and mortality by supplementing with vitamin D, a measure that is supported by high-quality research, has been absent from your frequent public broadcasts and professional bulletins.7  Optimizing nutrition is a convenient, inexpensive, and safe method of improving immune resistance and has been confirmed through numerous studies for both prevention and treatment of COVID-19. As far as I am aware, you have never mentioned something as simple as vitamin D supplements for our most vulnerable citizens. Yet, it was the promise to protect these same citizens that was used to justify the lockdown of a healthy population and the closure of businesses.

Why are you still using PCR testing? The Deputy Chief Medical Officer for Health in Ontario has publicly stated that the PCR test yields over 50% false positives. A New York Times investigative report found that PCR (truncated)

column36:
#MasterStressSaturdays
💥Are you feeling physical, mental, emotional stress? You're not alone.  But research shows that if you can learn how to treat yourself with greater compassion during difficult times, you can experience greater mental health & resilience.  

💥A simple exercise like inviting deep inhales and longer exhales helps us move to a place of compassion, calm and acceptance during these times.  

💥Also the longer exhalations stimulate the parasympathetic nervous system, which is the part of the nervous system that activates our relaxation response.  When we aren't letting the exhales out smoothly and deeply we continue supporting the cycle of stress and tension in the body.  

💥So anytime you are feeling anxious or stressed reconnect with your breath and emphasize the exhales so you can tap into your body's innate and natural relaxation response.

October 30, 2020
 
Dr. Brent Roussin​​​​​
4003 – 300 Carlton St. ​​​​

Brent.Roussin@gov.mb.ca​​​​

Mr. Brian Pallister
204 Legislative Building
450 Broadway
Winnipeg, MB
R3C 0V8
204-945-3714
Email: premier@leg.gov.mb.ca
 
Dear Mr. Pallister and Dr. Roussin,
 
I am writing this letter with the hope of gaining some clarity on the basis of your decision making that has led our provincial government, health ministry, regional health officers, hospitals, medical staff, businesses, and everyday citizens to follow pandemic policies that do not appear based on high-quality scientific research and, fact is, are doing everyone a great deal of harm.
In the beginning, we were all instructed that two weeks to “flatten the curve” would keep the health system from being overwhelmed. At the time we had little information on covid 19, how it was transmitted or the severity, so we were happy to “do our part”. Soon it became very apparent the overwhelming of the hospital system was not occurring, and now many physicians, whether they want to speak out or not, which is a whole other topic, question the appropriateness of public health policies.
Epidemiological evidence clearly shows that there never really was a pandemic, and the evidence has been available for at least 4-5 months, and is irrefutable. Yet in spite of this substantial research, your offices are continuing with the narrative that a pandemic still exists. This false story is being used to justify public health policies that have no health benefits, and have already caused considerable harm, and threaten to cause more harm in the future.
I would assume you are aware that Sweden took a very different approach than much of the world, and as of mid September, their infection rate reached an all time low, and covid related deaths were at zero. ZERO. Whereas 22 of 31 European countries, which enacted strict lockdowns had higher infection rates. Sweden has also saved their country from financial ruin and the mental health issues being experienced in many other countries including here and the U.S.A.
 
The numbers may have changed somewhat over a couple of days, but here is what I had as of three days ago for Manitoba. Lets look at it shall we:
Number of deaths: 60. That’s 1 in 25,000 and less than 1% of ALL deaths.
Number of ICU admissions: 15, which is 20% of all ICU beds. In a typical flu season, the majority of ICU beds are taken up by people with acute lung injury or pneumonia.
Number of hospitalizations: 83, which is less than 3% of all beds.
Percent usage of ventilator capacity (though ventilators should not be used as that has also proven to kill patients, as opposed to using, perhaps Hydroxychloroquine, zinc and azithromycin, which is proven to work): Less than 1%.
80% of the deaths in Canada are of people over the age of 85 and residents of personal care homes. Not much different than an actual flu season.
While we’re on that topic, it’s very interesting to note that incidents of the flu have gone down considerably this year! Reported so far is less than 10. How is that possible? In fact, Dr. Lawrence Rosenberg, Montreal’s medical officer has stated “this Covid virus is much like the seasonal flu”. A group of over 400 Belgian doctors have stated “Covid is not a killer virus, but a treatable condition”. Eighteen Canadian doctors wrote the Ontario Premier saying, “your policies risk significantly harming our children with lifelong consequences. We now see in Manitoba the same kind of policies being put forward to us.
In 2011, a review of the literature by the British Columbia Centres for Disease Control that sought to evaluate the effectiveness of social distancing measures such as school closures, travel restrictions, and limitations on mass gatherings as a means to address an influenza pandemic concluded that “such drastic restrictions are not economically feasible and are predicted to delay viral spread, but not impact overall mortality”. Specifically, there is no scientific or medical evidence for:
1. Self isolation of asymptomatic (healthy) people
2. Social distancing
3. Facemasks (which actually cause much more harm than good) please see: (truncated)

**UPDATE** - QUEBEC CITY GYM FORCED TO CLOSE AFTER DEFYING PUBLIC HEALTH LOCK-DOWN MEASURES

A Quebec City gym, which opened Thursday in defiance of the Legault government's lock-down measures, was forced by six police officers from four patrol vehicles to close yesterday. According to a witness, the gym will face further consequences if an attempt is made to reopen, including sealing the door shut. (1)

The decision by the owner to reopen was made as a coalition of 200 gyms and fitness centres was formed to willfully defy the lock-down measures by reopening on October 28th. While most of these have since backed down from their promise to reopen, a few brave owners decided to follow through and face the consequences.

At least three of the gym's members who were present at the time were also fined. The owner and patrons intend to contest the fines and force the government to justify their actions in a court of law. (1)

In Thetford Mines, another gym owner, François Madore, decided to reopen on Thursday morning, but has since faced no consequences. According to municipal police, Madore was approached by Sargent Yves Simoneau to discuss his intentions with reopening, to which Madore replied he intends to defy the orders. The police service will decide in the coming days whether or not to intervene. (2)

Madore is fully aware of the impact and consequences of his decisions and has stated, "I will not pay the fines and they can put me in jail." (2)

As more business owners defy public health decrees to try and save their means of subsistance, will governments dare to test the legality of their decrees in court?

**MISE À JOUR** - UN GYM DE QUÉBEC EST FORCÉ À FERMER APRÈS AVOIR DÉFIÉ LES MESURES DE LA SANTÉ PUBLIQUE

Un gymnase de Québec, qui a ouvert jeudi au mépris des mesures sanitaires du gouvernement Legault, a été contraint par six policiers de quatre véhicules de patrouille à fermer hier. Selon un témoin, le gymnase devra faire face à d'autres conséquences si une tentative de réouverture est faite, y compris en fermant la porte par l'application d'une scellé. (1)

column31: Here’s the letter. Don’t forget to sign it then please send by email, and also print a physical copy and send by regular mail! Let’s inundate them with letters! And feel free to share with anyone you know who is on “our side” and understands what we’re dealing with. October 30, 2020 Dr. Brent Roussin​​​​​ 4003 – 300 Carlton St. ​​​​ Winnipeg, MB ​​​​​ R3B 3M9​​​​​​ Brent.Roussin@gov.mb.ca​​​​ ​​​​​​​ Mr. Brian Pallister 204 Legislative Building 450 Broadway Winnipeg, MB R3C 0V8 204-945-3714 Email: premier@leg.gov.mb.ca Dear Mr. Pallister and Dr. Roussin, I am writing this letter with the hope of gaining some clarity on the basis of your decision making that has led our provincial government, health ministry, regional health officers, hospitals, medical staff, businesses, and everyday citizens to follow pandemic policies that do not appear based on high-quality scientific research and, fact is, are doing everyone a great deal of harm. In the beginning, we were all instructed that two weeks to “flatten the curve” would keep the health system from being overwhelmed. At the time we had little information on covid 19, how it was transmitted or the severity, so we were happy to “do our part”. Soon it became very apparent the overwhelming of the hospital system was not occurring, and now many physicians, whether they want to speak out or not, which is a whole other topic, question the appropriateness of public health policies. Epidemiological evidence clearly shows that there never really was a pandemic, and the evidence has been available for at least 4-5 months, and is irrefutable. Yet in spite of this substantial research, your offices are continuing with the narrative that a pandemic still exists. This false story is being used to justify public health policies that have no health benefits, and have already caused considerable harm, and threaten to cause more harm in the future. I would assume you are aware that Sweden took a very different approach than much of the world, and as of mid September, their infection rate reached an all time low, and covid related deaths were at zero. ZERO. Whereas 22 of 31 European countries, which enacted strict lockdowns had higher infection rates. Sweden has also saved their country from financial ruin and the mental health issues being experienced in many other countries including here and the U.S.A. The numbers may have changed somewhat over a couple of days, but here is what I had as of three days ago for Manitoba. Lets look at it shall we: Number of deaths: 60. That’s 1 in 25,000 and less than 1% of ALL deaths. Number of ICU admissions: 15, which is 20% of all ICU beds. In a typical flu season, the majority of ICU beds are taken up by people with acute lung injury or pneumonia. Number of hospitalizations: 83, which is less than 3% of all beds. Percent usage of ventilator capacity (though ventilators should not be used as that has also proven to kill patients, as opposed to using, perhaps Hydroxychloroquine, zinc and azithromycin, which is proven to work): Less than 1%. 80% of the deaths in Canada are of people over the age of 85 and residents of personal care homes. Not much different than an actual flu season. While we’re on that topic, it’s very interesting to note that incidents of the flu have gone down considerably this year! Reported so far is less than 10. How is that possible? In fact, Dr. Lawrence Rosenberg, Montreal’s medical officer has stated “this Covid virus is much like the seasonal flu”. A group of over 400 Belgian doctors have stated “Covid is not a killer virus, but a treatable condition”. Eighteen Canadian doctors wrote the Ontario Premier saying, “your policies risk significantly harming our children with lifelong consequences. We now see in Manitoba the same kind of policies being put forward to us. In 2011, a review of the literature by the British Columbia Centres for Disease Control that sought to evaluate the effectiveness of social distancing measures such as school closures, travel restrictions, and limitations on mass gatherings as a means to address an influenza pandemic concluded that “such drastic restrictions are not economically feasible and are predicted to delay viral spread, but not impact overall mortality”. Specifically, there is no scientific or medical evidence for: 1. Self isolation of asymptomatic (healthy) people 2. Social distancing 3. Facemasks (which actually cause much more harm than good) please see: https://www.researchgate.net/profile/D_Rancourt/publication/343399832_Face_masks_lies_damn_lies_and_public_health_officials_A_growing_body_of_evidence/links/5f282ef0458515b729ff3f82/Face-masks-lies-damn-lies-and-public-health-officials-A-growing-body-of-evidence.pdf?origin=publication_detail https://vaccinechoicecanada.com/in-the-news/who-new-guidelines-on-masking/ (truncated)

Based on this singular but very important metric, deaths, Sweden's strategy to not implement lockdowns and mask orders can only be viewed as a success. While other countries continue to suffer more deaths, they do not.

LES DÉCÈS EN SUÈDE CONTINUENT À DÉFIER LA TENDANCE DES PAYS EUROPÉENS CONFINÉS / MASQUÉS

Les preuves épidémiologiques sur les décès quotidiens du Covid-19 en Suède sont claires: il n'y a pas de tendance à la hausse comme dans les autres pays européens.

Sur la base de cette métrique singulière mais très importante, les décès, la stratégie suédoise de ne pas mettre en œuvre les confinements et les masques obligatoires ne peut être considérée que comme un succès. There's lots of changes to our educational system that Ohio Advocates for Medical Freedom can't support. Many of the sweeping, one-sized-fits-all solutions that many Ohio school districts have implemented at the direction of state and local health departments are unhealthy for children, in our opinion.

For example, we believe that universal face masks and/or face shields, overuse of hand sanitizers, and disinfectant aerosolized into classrooms could potentially be an unknown health concern for students.

We also believe that the distance learning, social distancing, and decreased non-verbal communication could pose an unknown mental health and/or developmental concern for students.

We applaud Superintendent, John Marschhausen, Ph.D., of Hilliard City Schools, for addressing mental health concerns in a message he put out to district staff earlier this week.

Source: https://vimeo.com/473090685/50639716e3

"Between April and June, when the coronavirus first spread, rates of anxiety and depression increased substantially across the U.S., with 41% of adults reporting at least one adverse behavioral or mental health condition by the end of June, according to data from the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. Overall, 10.7% of people surveyed by the CDC reported they had seriously considered suicide within the past 30 days."

Source: https://tinyurl.com/yya5nxt4

While Hilliard City Schools approach to mitigating the impact of Covid-19 to student and staff's physical health may remain up for debate, we appreciate Superintendent Marschhausen's effort to address the mental health concerns of students and staff within his district.

Policy makers in our health departments, governor's office, legislature, and within the federal government should take note of these concerns and better balance them with policy decisions that are currently based on an unobtainable goal of eradicating this illness, one that many health professionals cannot even clinically differentiate from the Flu.

Do you believe that the risk to student's physical health outweighs any possible impact on their mental health? Or visa versa? What do you think?

column36:
STATUS OF NOV. 3rd ELECTION - 128th DISTRICT

Based on preliminary unofficial reports, it appears that I may not get the most votes in yesterday’s 128th District General Election.  But the votes are preliminary unofficial numbers  and are subject to major changes for the counting the mail-in ballots which could exceed 50% of the votes cast yesterday.  Therefore, it’s too early to make conclusions.

Nonetheless, it is very clear that the probable outcome shows this campaign doing considerably better than we have done in any previous campaign for the 128th.

That said, I offer various points for which the outcome at this point does not show me having most votes.

1.  There were various voters who did not vote for me because they thought that as Democrats, they were allowed only to vote on the Democrat line.  This ridiculous notion has been promoted by devious unscrupulous operatives even at the local level.

2.  Trying to get reasonable service from the U.S. Postal Service has been for me in this election a hair-puller.  Since the Aug. 11th Primary, this campaign has paid for and sent five district-wide flyers to 11,000 registered voters at an average cost of $3,700 (of which approx. $2,000 each went for postage).  Yet despite multiple pleas by me to the local Postmaster and multiple assurances by him, about 20% of the total mailed pieces never reached their proper destination.

3.  My opponent, the incumbent Chris Rosario, has an extremely ambitious, zealous and even bully campaign operative, Wanda Geter Pataky.  Given how I have observed her to act in public, based also on what has been reported regarding her mishandling of absentee ballots, and considering what I have known of how she abuses her city employment to boost her Justice-of-the-Peace “business”, it is apparent that she would do almost anything to win.

4.  Biased media reporting!  Facebook has been another frustration.  Its usual accommodating practices for boosting commercial ads were wholly surpassed by full suppression of ALL of our conservative political adds (not so for ads boosted by local Dem candidates) and even considerable delay in publishing mere personal posts of material of conservative political content.  In addition, the CT Post’s article of Nov. 2nd by the ultra-liberal Ken Dixon entitled “Main issue in state House races?  The presidency” was, in my view, an attempt to evade real state partisan issues to make a politically biased opinion a reality.  Unfortunately, it was partially successful.

5.  Early voting tilts an election in favor of the status quo.  Where a challenge candidate is vigorously going against a distorted and corrupt system, it will take some time to develop political issues and/or time to complete a rigorous door-knocking program.  So if a voter sends in a vote a month before the election in a four-month official election period, then the voter is precluded from considering an important one-quarter of political material which could impact his vote.  Also, for a ten-week door-knocking program, the early mail-in ballot negates 40% of the door-knocking, often considered to be the most effective campaigning practice.  Thus, allowing mass early voting tends to suppress the intent of the Democratic system.

5.  Rosario continues to get a residual benefit from a pattern of the suppression by City of Shelton officials of politically-sensitive information with implications for Rosario, a situation which is the subject of a federal lawsuit which I recently presented against the City of Shelton, its Mayor and its Chief of Police.

6.  On Oct. 28th, Rosario even got early votes from the Justices of the CT Supreme Court.  Those votes were in the form of the denial of Petition for Certification which I presented regarding an egregiously defective long-running mortgage foreclosure proceeding, a matter with the most recent contorted stage having been administered in Bridgeport Superior Court by Judge Walter Spadar.   The high Court issued its summary decision with no explanation denying a Petition focusing primarily on a rather straightforward procedural matter only seven weeks after it was filed and just five days before the General Election.  So what’s the significance of the Supreme Court action?  It is rather well known in and outside our state courts that I have been an advocate of fixing our broken judicial system, of exposing and ending the courts’ systematic biases and in challenging the network of vested interests which drive and “motivate” the courts’ machinery.  One could say that I am an unelected counterpart to 3rd District Rep. Minnie Gonzalez (D-Hartford) for being a zealous advocate of judicial reform.  In contrast, Rosario, who has been the epitome of a good ole’ boy, sitting by when members of the Jidiciary Committee give judicial nominees mainly softball questions rather than any meaningful challenge.  Consider how the State Police and the Milford State’s Attorney (truncated)

I, in my bathrobe
With a cat in my lap,
Had shut off the TV,
tired of political crap.
When all of a sudden,
There arose such a noise 
I peered out my window, 
Saw Pelosi and her boys.
They had come for my wallet,
They wanted my pay 
To hand out to others 
Who had not worked a day.
They snatched up my money, 
And quick as a wink, 
Jumped back on their bandwagon 
As I gagged from the stink.
She then rallied her henchmen 
Who were pulling her cart. 
I could tell they were out 
To tear my country apart.
On Biden, on Harris,
On Schumer and Libs 
On Bug Eyes, on Waters 
She screamed at the pairs.
They took off for her cause,
And as they flew out of sight, 
I heard her laugh at a nation 
Who wouldn't stand up and fight.
So I leave you to think
On this one final note:
IF YOU DON'T WANT SOCIALISM

column31: San Diego went into Purple Tier today! Submit a written comment online for the SanDiego Board of Supervisors' meeting BEFORE Tuesday at 9 am. Instructions: Go to “eComment on Board of Supervisors Agenda Items” sandiegocounty.gov/content/sdc/bos/ecomment.html Note: You will only be able to post one comment, and if you make an error, you will not be able to revise it. Also, call and email the Board. Tell them to end the lockdowns/state of emergency - they have the power to do that and tell them to stop following the state Tier system. Contact info: https://www.sandiegocounty.gov/general/bos.html Also, sign up BEFORE 9 am to speak at the meeting (you have to call in). Instructions to join the meeting: 1. SUBMIT THIS ONLINE FORM before 8:55am on Nov. 17 www.sandiegocounty.gov/content/sdc/bos/telecomments-tues.html Select Agenda Item #8 “UPDATE ON COVID-19 RESPONSE” 2. On Nov. 17 WATCH THE MEETING on TV or online (Cox Ch. 24 or Ch. 19, Spectrum Ch. 24 or Ch. 85, streaming live on sandiegocounty.gov and youtube/countysandiego) 3. When Agenda Item #8 “COVID-19 RESPONSE” begins, CALL the number you received from the County via email. Turn off the volume on your device. You will hear the Board of Supervisors meeting on your phone. 4. When it is your time to speak, the Clerk will unmute your phone. You will hear a beep, and the Clerk will ask you to state your name. START SPEAKING. This happens without prior warning; it might be a little awkward. If you miss your turn, don’t worry; the Clerk will return to your call later. Note: Be prepared to be on the phone for a LONG TIME, one to two hours, maybe longer. You will be on hold during the meeting and during the comment portion of Agenda Item #8. You will not know where you are in line to speak. Why a teleconference? Due to the current restrictions, the Board of Supervisors and the Public are not able to attend these meetings in person.
